<HEAD>
<TITLE>WaterTransport.html</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="paper3.jpg">
<CENTER><FONT SIZE=6>Water Transport</FONT></CENTER>
<HR SIZE=4 WIDTH=50% ALIGN=CENTER>
<TABLE CELLPADDING=5 BORDER=0><TR><TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP 
COLSPAN=30><FONT SIZE=5>Task</FONT></TD> <TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP 
COLSPAN=80><FONT SIZE=5>To move clients, staff or goods on 
water</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P ALIGN="LEFT">Water-based travel can be an important component of 
energy consumption for island-based 
facilities and tour operations.
<P>
<TABLE CELLPADDING=5 BORDER=0><TR><TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP 
COLSPAN=30><FONT SIZE=5>Action</FONT></TD><TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP 
COLSPAN=80><FONT SIZE=5>Select fuel-efficient water transport</FONT></TD> 
</TR>

<TR><TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP COLSPAN=30><FONT SIZE=5>Issues</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP COLSPAN=80><UL>
<LI>Sailing is much more fuel-efficient than motorised water travel. Use 
sailboats in preference to motorboats, when feasible.</UL></TD></TR>
<TR><TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP COLSPAN=30></TD><TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP 
COLSPAN=80><UL>
<LI>Standard fuel consumption data for boats are not available because of 
the variety of hull/fitout/engine combinations. Record fuel consumption 
data and swap information 
with fellow operators to identify fuel-efficient options.</UL></TD></TR>
<TR><TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP COLSPAN=30></TD><TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP 
COLSPAN=80><UL>
<LI>Diesel engines are more fuel-efficient than petrol ones, and diesel 
fuel has a lower 
fire risk. Light Fuel Oil (LFO) has no environmental benefits over diesel 
fuel, and 
costs about the same as diesel fuel.</UL></TD></TR>
<TR><TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP COLSPAN=30></TD><TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP 
COLSPAN=80><UL>
<LI>Four-stroke engines are generally quieter and more fuel-efficient 
than conventional 
two-stroke engines.</UL></TD></TR>
<TR><TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP COLSPAN=30></TD><TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP 
COLSPAN=80><UL>
<LI>New boat designs and engine technologies (such as orbital engines for 
outboards) are 
becoming more fuel-efficient. Collect comparative information when buying 
a new boat.</UL></TD></TR></TABLE>
<TABLE CELLPADDING=5 BORDER=0><TR><TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP 
COLSPAN=30><FONT SIZE=5>Action</FONT></TD><TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP 
COLSPAN=80><FONT SIZE=5>Operate boats more efficiently</FONT></TD></TR>

<TR><TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP COLSPAN=30><FONT SIZE=5>Issues</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP COLSPAN=80><UL>
<LI>Fuel consumption of most boats increases dramatically at high speed. 
Reduce speed 
by a few kilometres per hour and save fuel.</UL></TD></TR>
<TR><TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP COLSPAN=30></TD><TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP 
COLSPAN=80><UL>
<LI>Ensure engines and drives are properly maintained, and that hulls are 
kept clean to 
minimise drag.</UL></TD></TR>
<TR><TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP COLSPAN=30></TD><TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP 
COLSPAN=80><UL>
<LI>Leaving an engine idling for long periods wastes fuel. Switch it 
off.</UL></TD></TR>
<TR><TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP COLSPAN=30></TD><TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP 
COLSPAN=80><UL>
<LI>Minimise and eliminate oil leaks from motors and drives by good 
inspection and maintenance 
practices.</UL></TD></TR></TABLE>
<TABLE CELLPADDING=5 BORDER=0><TR><TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP 
COLSPAN=30><FONT SIZE=5>Action</FONT></TD><TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP 
COLSPAN=80><FONT SIZE=5>Avoid dumping sewage</FONT></TD></TR>

<TR><TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP COLSPAN=30><FONT SIZE=5>Issues</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP COLSPAN=80><UL>
<LI>More harbours are providing sewage pump-out facilities for boats, to 
reduce the dumping 
of nutrient-rich wastes in often-sensitive marine environments. Use 
facilities if 
they exist, and seek their provision if they do 
not.</UL></TD></TR></TABLE> 
<HR WIDTH=90% SIZE=4 ALIGN=CENTER>
<FONT SIZE=5><B>Success stories</B></FONT>

<P ALIGN="LEFT">Tasmania's West Coast Charters uses wind-powered yachts 
for its operation, and saves 
around $6 000 per annum on fuel. The reduction in noise pollution is 
attractive to 
clients.
<P ALIGN="LEFT">The Yellow Waters Resort in Kakadu in the Northern 
Territory has replaced all of its 
two-stroke outboard engines with four-stroke alternatives. These are 
quieter, cheaper 
to operate, use less fuel and emit less smoke and oil.
<P>
Caption: Four-stroke outboard engines provide quiter and more energy 
efficient<BR>
 tours at Yellow Waters in Kakadu National Park, Northern Territory
<IMG VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 BORDER=4  SRC="Pics/River1.jpg">
</BODY>
</HTML>
</DOC>
