<HTML>
<TITLE> Opportunities at Crisscross</TITLE>
<BODY bgcolor=#FFFFFF>
<IMG SRC=crisscross.gif>


<P><H2>We are currently looking for the following staff:</H2>
<UL>
<LI><B>Operations Manager</B>
<UL>
<LI>Are a Japanese speaker who knows how to build networks and has strong marketing skills? Help us grow crisscross into Japan's number one Internet provider.


<P><B>So what is there to do? Just a few things...</B>
<BR>
<UL>
<LI>Build an interenet backbone throughout japan asap 
<LI>Hire friendly and competent staff
<LI>Building database-based websites including classified systems, web-BBS's and online shopping systems 
<LI>Organize a sales team for the above item.
<LI>Look after our webserver and organize user support.
<LI>Deal with NTT
<BR>
<LI>Publicize our services like crazy.
<BR>

We are already aggressively marketing our services and our customer base is growing rapidly. We are already in the Japan Times, Daily Yomiuri, Internet Magazine and PC fan with more to come.
<BR>
</UL>
</UL>
<BR>

<BR>
<LI><B> Webmaster <--> Art Director</B>
<UL>We will be adding 12 new pages to Tokyo Classified over the next few months and hope you can take the project to the next level and beyond. In addition, we will be expanding our website to make it one of the most informative and lively places on the web. Join us as we grow!

<P>There is a lot of overlap in these positions: We are looking for either a designer with good technical knowledge or separate designer and technical persons.


<P><B>Webmaster Responsibilities:</B> <BR>
Upkeep of CRISSCROSS Website.<BR> 
Upkeep of Tokyo Classified site.<BR>
Some user support.<BR>

<P>Requirements: HTML, MacOS, UNIX, SQL.


<P><B>Art Director Responsibilities: </B><BR>
Art Direction for Tokyo Classified: You will be working with our layout staff, directing ad and feature design.
Art Direction of all CRISSCROSS and Tokyo Classified Websites.

<P>Requirements: Photoshop, Illustrator, HTML. Please do not apply if you cannot match the standard of recent Tokyo Classified covers.
</UL>
<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Technical Support Staff </B>

<UL>
<LI>If you are a Japanese native speaker who knows Macintosh, Windows95 and 3.1 and can write HTML we would like to meet you!
</UL>

</UL>
</UL>


<P>We are looking for candidates who can fit in with our team spirit: Open, efficient, helpful, flexible and friendly. 

<P>We offer a good basic salary, performance-related bonus and lots of opportunity to grow with us.
<BR>
<P>If you think you are suitable for the above positions please
email your resume to <A HREF=mailto:sparky@crisscross.com>Sparky</A>.

<P>Hope to hear from you soon.

</FONT>

</BODY>
