<HTML>
<TITLE>30,000yen Unlimited ISDN 64K Access</TITLE>
<body bgcolor=#FFFFFF>
<IMG SRC=crisscross.gif>

<H3>The wait is over!</H3>

<FONT SIZE=4>It came from a hole in the road dug by NTT, through a rather ordinary pipe, up to the sixth floor, 
through the celing and down into a sinister, very expensive,  black box. There it sits humming softly like the 
sentinel in 2001. But what is it? Oh no! It can't be! It's.....<b>64K ISDN access from CRISSCROSS!!</b>

<P>We are happy to announce that we have completed installation of 92 64k ISDN lines into CRISSCROSS tower. 
We can pass on the benefits of our new technology directly to you, offering full 64K ISDN unlimited access 
for one year at what we think is the lowest price in Japan - 30,000yen. This is in line with our commitment to 
fast, friendly and reasonable internet services.

<P>We have upgraded all of our servers to 166MHz Pentium machines running Windows NT, ensuring that our 
customers have trouble-free email and speedy access.

<P><b>What is ISDN?</b>

<P>ISDN is a system for sending digital signals over ordinary metallic telephone lines, like the one in 
your home. One metallic line can have two 64K channels which can be combined to make a rather speedy 128K access. 

<P>If your current modem is 28.8kbps you will be able to access the web and download files almost 
<b>THREE TIMES FASTER.</B>

<P><A HREF="http://www.crisscross.com/access/ISDN_HowTo.html">How do I get connected?</A>

</FONT>
</DOC>
