<TITLE>Doug Berger, M.D., Ph.D., Psychiatrist, Psychotherapist in Japan</TITLE>
<META name="description" content="Dr. Berger is doing psychotherapy and counseling in Tokyo. He is a bilingual (English and Japanese) American Board-Certified psychiatrist ."><META name="keywords" content="Counseling, Psychotherapy, Japan, Tokyo, Psychotherapist, Psychiatrist, English, Japanese"></HEAD>
<BODYBGCOLOR=#123456>
<FONT SIZE[R><Home Page Html by Doug Berger, 9-11/96)   <META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Mozilla/3.0Gold (Win95; I) [Netscape]"><BODY TEXT="#000000"  BODYBGCOLOR=#000000 onLoad="timerONE=window.setTimeout('scrollit_r2l(100)',500);"><P><SCRIPT LANGUAGE="JavaScript"><!-- Beginning of JavaScript Applet -------------------function scrollit_r2l(seedval){        var m1  = "How much of human behavior is predetermined at birth?";        var m2  = " To what degree does our unconscious govern how we think?";        var m3  =" What constitutes experiences like 'Identity' and 'Happiness'?";        var m4  = "      These are the questions that make study of the human experience fascinating.";        var msg=m1+m2+m3+m4;        var out = " ";        var c   = 1;        if (seedval > 100) {                seedval--;                var cmd="scrollit_r2l(" + seedval + ")";                timerTwo=window.setTimeout(cmd,100);        }        else if (seedval <= 100 && seedval > 0) {                for (c=0 ; c < seedval ; c++) {                        out+=" ";                }                out+=msg;                seedval--;                var cmd="scrollit_r2l(" + seedval + ")";                    window.status=out;                timerTwo=window.setTimeout(cmd,100);        }        else if (seedval <= 0) {                if (-seedval < msg.length) {                        out+=msg.substring(-seedval,msg.length);                        seedval--;                        var cmd="scrollit_r2l(" + seedval + ")";                        window.status=out;                        timerTwo=window.setTimeout(cmd,100);                }                else {                        window.status=" ";                        timerTwo=window.setTimeout("scrollit_r2l(100)",75);                }        }}// -- End of JavaScript code -------------- --></SCRIPT><A NAME="TopOfPage"></A></P>

<CENTER><BR><TABLE BORDER="7"><TD><img src="Images/Kabin.gif" ALT="Red Vase With Plant. Computer scan of photo (original: oil on canvas Circa 1955)." width=222 height="250"></TD> </TABLE></CENTER><H2><Center><HW_HEADLINE>

Doug Berger, M.D., Ph.D., Psychiatrist

</HW_HEADLINE></Center>

</H2>

<HW_SEE>

<P>





<NOBR>





</strong>

 







</NOBR>





<HW_INSERT>

<HW_TWIS>



<P>

<BR><HW_SUPPLEMENTAL>





<BR>















<P>

Dr. Berger is an <A HREF="http://www.psych.org/med_ed/abpn_sec1.html">American Board-Certified Psychiatrist</A> conducting psychotherapy and counseling in both English and Japanese, and psychiatric research in Tokyo, Japan. He has published a number of articles on topics including, suicide in medical patients and the attitudes of physicians towards these patients, eating disorders, dissociative disorders and child abuse, parental bonding, schizophrenia, cross-cultural issues related to Japan, and psychiatric drug 
development in Japan (See for example an 
article in <A HREF="http://science-mag.aaas.org/science/scripts/display/full/273/5273/318.html"><I>SCIENCE</I></A> magazine).  Dr. Berger has also given a 
number of presentations on these and other topics at various international 
conferences. <P>Inquires on counseling and psychotherapy in Japan  can be addressed  to Dr. Berger at <strong>Tel: +81-3-3716-6624. </strong>

   <P> Click one of the items below for further information.




</P>

</P>








