<HTML><TITLE> Crisscross 20,000 Unlimited Access</TITLE><BODY bgcolor=#FFFFFF><CENTER><IMG SRC=Unlimited.gif><IMG SRC=UnlimitedE.gif><H3>Why you should choose Crisscross... </H3>The two most important which are important when choosing an internet provider:<BR> bandwidth and modem ratio. <H3>10:1 Modem ratio</H3>Modem ratio refers to the number of telephone lines with a modem, in relation to the number of members. A modem ratio of one modem for every 10 users is considered to be a very good service. Some providers may only have a ratio of one modem to 30 users, which can mean busy signals and a long wait until lines become free for your connection<H3>High Bandwidth ratio</H3>Bandwidth refers to the capacity of the line available for the flow of data back and forth. If too many users try to use a limited bandwidth, the flow gets clogged, which means you have to wait.The bandwidth in relation to the number of users is much more important than not the absolute bandwidth. For example 128K for 200 users is better than 512K for 5,000 users.<H3>Our Guarantee</H3>At Crisscross we guarantee a modem ratio of 1 modem for every 10 users. We also guarantee to maintain our bandwidth ratio which means that you will spend less time waiting and more time finding the information you want.<H3>Plus...Technical Support in English</H3>Our technical support stsff are here to answer any of your questions. Call us or send email to <A HREF=mailto:support@crisscross.com>support@crisscross.com</A><P><HR></FONT></CENTER></BODY>
