<HTML>
<TITLE>Making your Homepage!</TITLE>
<body bgcolor=#FFFFFF>
<IMG SRC=MakeHomePage.gif>

<BR>
<BR>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=5>
CRISSCROSS gives all our members 10 Megabytes of disk space free!
You can use this to make your own personal home page.
Read on to see how easy it is!
</FONT>
<P>
<HR>

<H3>FIRST THINGS FIRST...</H3>
<FONT SIZE=4>

The first thing you have to do is to <A HREF="mailto:support@crisscross.com">send us a note</A> asking us to set up a homepage directory for you.
    
<P>Then you can upload HTML files and graphics into your directory to a maximum of 10MB. You can upload and download files to the directory using any FTP compliant program. 

<P>For Macintosh you can download Fetch 
<BR>
<BR>
<H3>HOW TO CONNECT AND UPLOAD FILES</H3>
<P>Open your FTP program<BR>
Click 'Open Connection...' and fill in the following...
<BR>
<BR>
<TABLE BORDER=0>
<TR><TD>Host:       <TD>ftp.crisscross.com or 202.243.58.6
<TR><TD>UserID:     <TD>Your UserID
<TR><TD>Password:   <TD>Your Password
<TR><TD>Directory:  <TD>/YourUserID/
</TABLE>
<P>Click OK.You will see the login screen. If you have a problem please email <A HREF=mailto:support@crisscross.com>support@crisscross.com</A>

<BR>
<BR>
<BR>

<H3>HOW TO MAKE YOUR HOME PAGE</H3>

<P>Webpages are made using HTML (HyperText Markup Language). You have to use HTML tags to format the page. You can use any text editor to write the tags, but if you are going to make a lot of pages we recommend you use a dedicated HTML editing program such as Adobe PageMill.

<P>Make a text file called "default.html". Copy the following into it:

<PRE>
<CODE>&lt;HTML&gt;</CODE>
<CODE>&lt;TITLE&gt;</CODE>My HomePage<CODE>&lt;/TITLE&gt;</CODE>
<CODE>&lt;BODY BGCOLOR=#123456&gt;</CODE>
<CODE>&lt;H1&gt;</CODE>This is my HomePage<CODE>&lt;/H1&gt;</CODE>
Hey this is cool! I've got my own page!
<CODE>&lt;A HREF=http://www.crisscross.com/&gt;</CODE>Where does this link go?<CODE>&lt;/A&gt;</CODE>
<CODE>&lt;/BODY&gt;</CODE>
<CODE>&lt;/HTML&gt;</CODE>
</PRE>

<P>Upload the file to your crisscross directory (format should be Raw Data). 


<P>You can access your homepage with the following URL: 
<B>http://www.crisscross.com/users/yourUserID/default.html</B>

<P>Remember that noone will see your page unless you give them the URL or they come through the crisscross users homepage. 

<P>Play around with the above and see what you can do. The best way to find out how to make your own pages is to look on the web itself! Have a look at the HTML guides in <A HREF=http://www.yahoo.com/Computers_and_Internet/Software/Data_Formats/HTML/Guides_and_Tutorials/>yahoo</A>. There are lots of sites with buttons and graphics you can use (you can also take things from other websites by holding down the mouse button on the item and selecting 'copy to hard disk'. Please remember to ask for permission.

<P>Another useful tip is to go to a page which has a design you like and select View-Document Source from Netscape's menubar. You will see the HTML that makes up the page.

<P>To test your page before you put it on the web just drag the file onto Netscape. 
<BR>
<BR>
<BR>

<H3>THINGS TO TRY</H3>

<UL>
<LI>Add your own text and play with text formating tags
<LI>Add a backgound pattern with <CODE>&lt;BODY BACKGOUND=MyBackground.jpg&gt;</CODE>  . You can find some <A HREF=http://www.yahoo.com/Computers_and_Internet/Internet/World_Wide_Web/Programming/Backgrounds/>here</A>
    
<LI>Upload a graphic and make it display on the page 
        <B><CODE>&lt;IMG SRC=myphoto.gif&gt;</CODE></B>. 
<LI> Make a second page and make a link from the first to the second
        <B><CODE>&lt;A HREF=Page2&gt;</CODE>This is a link to page 2<CODE>&lt;/A&gt;</CODE></B>
<LI> Organise your work. Put all your graphics in a new folder called
        "Graphics" and call them using <B><CODE>&lt;IMG SRC=Graphics/Myphoto.gif&gt;</CODE></B>
</UL>
<BR>


<H3>THINGS TO WATCH OUT FOR</H3>
<UL>
<LI>Dont put any spaces in file names
<LI>A missing / or " can make a big difference. 
<LI>Graphics should be in gif or jpg format eg. mygraphic.gif or mygraphic.jpg
<LI>Test, test and test again BEFORE it goes on the web.
<LI>Ask a friend to help if you can't make graphics. Otherwise you may end up with the CRISSCROSS ugly page award :) 
<LI>Nothing commercial or immoral please.
<LI>No sex sites or sex links sites please.
</UL>


<P>If you are really stuck, send webpage problems to <A HREF=mailto:support@crisscross.com>support@crisscross.com</A>
<P>Once you have got your home page set up send us some email and we will add the address to the CRISSCROSS user homepage list.

<P>Happy pagemaking!
    
Sparky

</FONT>
</DOC>
