<HTML>

<HEAD>

<TITLE>BAD ROOM</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff" LINK="#ff5a08" ALINK="#ff5a08" VLINK="#ff5a08"
TEXT="#1e1611">
<font face=helvetica>
<center>
<IMG SRC="biene.jpg" vspace=10><br>

<nobr><IMG SRC="lb.gif" vspace=5><IMG SRC="lo.gif" vspace=5><br></nobr>
<font size=+5><TT>BAD ROOM</TT></FONT SIZE=+5></center)<p><br>
<h3>Ambient Description</h3>

<table width=600><TR><TD>
<P align=left><font size=+1>October in Helsinki - it's cold and windy - the window of the MUU-Base is
almost closed, because someone nailed wooden panels across it - but the gaps
between the panels allow a look inside - the entrance is like always - you
enter the room.

It is a yellow-brownish light in that room - very bright -  and it is
rather hot (we can manage this becouse of the strong spots) - it is not 
very nice to breath because of the stickyness of the air  - it smells a 
little bit -  it's a long time ago since somebody let fresh air in. There 
are 3 big wooden boxes standing around - boxes which are used for transportation 
on cargo-ships. They are closed with big nails and they look like having been 
on a long journey - (may be this movie comes to your mind where they transport 
boxes filled with rotten dynamite) - the floor you walk on is soft - 
it is covered with earth, sawdust and dry hey which is obviously also inside 
the wooden boxes - you can see it coming through the cracks hindering you from
looking at the real content - an old metal gascan is in one corner - in 
the other one there are 3 metal cubes - parts of a machine - maybe to cool 
down something - 4 oiltins of 10 litres each, as used by  restaurants,  
are besides one wooden box - somebody took away the top so that they look like pails.</FONT SIZE=+1>
</TD></TR></table>

<H3>The Sound</H3>
<table width=600><TR><TD>
<P align=left><font size=+1>You have the feeling that there are a lot of insects caught inside these
objects - trying to get out - you hear every now and then this buzzing
getting louder, which happens when flying insects are clashing against a
thin metal wall or glass - when you look very carefully you see the tins
moving in this moments - but you hear also other sounds which remind you
immediately that you haven't been at the dentist's since to long - the
noises of dentists' drills in action - very soft, but impossible not to be
recognized -</FONT SIZE=+1></P></TD></TR></table>
<table width=600><TR><TD>
<A href="matsyl.htm"><B>fuchs-eckerman</B><BR></A></TD></TR></table>
<NOBR><A HREF="matsyl.htm"><IMG SRC="../links.gif" border=0></A><A
HREF="http://www.t0.or.at/~fuchs-eckermann/"><IMG SRC="../rechts.gif" border=0></A></NOBR>
</BODY>
</HTML>
