<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>ENTREE/SORTIE</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff" LINK="#ff5a08" ALINK="#ff5a08" VLINK="#ff5a08"TEXT="#000000"><CENTER><P><TABLE WIDTH=604> <TR><TD COLSPAN=2><IMG vspace=15 SRC="door.jpg"><P></TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN=2><font size=+5>ENTREE/SORTIE</FONT SIZE=+5></TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN=2><FONT SIZE=+1><P ALIGN=LEFT>26 Doors, recorded in Vienna, february 1990, were assembled in a little "sound&amp;vision" package. They were intended to serve as a sound vocabulary and starting material. These sounds had been sent to artists in various cities, accompanied by the pictures, in order to be transformed and aranged by them. The result of the exchange was broadcast by Kunstradio.<br><Br>Composers: Igor Lintz-Mau&eacute;s <FONT SIZE=-1>(Brazil)</FONT SIZE=-1>...Mathias Fuchs <FONT SIZE=-1>(Austria)</FONT SIZE=-1>...Lisa Sirois <FONT SIZE=-1>(USA)</FONT SIZE=-1>...Zora-Maria Bauer <FONT SIZE=-1>(Germany)</FONT SIZE=-1>...Edwin Pfanzagel<FONT SIZE=-1>(Austria)</FONT SIZE=-1>...Elisabeth Schimana <FONT SIZE=-1>(Austria)</FONT SIZE=-1>...Simon Waters <FONT SIZE=-1>(UK)</FONT SIZE=-1>...Martin Ebner, Lydia Lindner, Wolfgang Tockner <FONT SIZE=-1>(Austria)</FONT SIZE=-1>...Rik Rue <FONT SIZE=-1>(Australia)</FONT SIZE=-1>...Gunter Schneider <FONT SIZE=-1>(Austria)</FONT SIZE=-1></TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN=2><A href="matsyl.htm"><B>fuchs-eckerman</B></A></TD></TR></TABLE><NOBR><A HREF="link.htm"><IMG SRC="../links.gif" border=0></A><A HREF="1991.htm"><IMG SRC="../rechts.gif" border=0></A></NOBR></CENTER></BODY></HTML>
