<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>SoundCollection</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY  link=#c00000 vlink=#c00000" alink=#c00000>
<basefont size=3>
<H1>SoundCollection / Japan</H1>

<a href="calendar.htm"><img src="sinfo/slogos.jpg" align="right" border="0"></a>
There are probably two modes of listening to sounds on the network: <font color=#c0000>quick &amp; dirty</font> or <font color=#c0000>clean &amp; slow</font>
<UL>1. the quick-response "click &amp; go" browsing activitiy<BR>
- mainly interested in content/ <font color=#c0000>Bedeutung</font><BR>
(Where does the sound point to? A certain rock band? A guitar type? A dress code? A certain country?)

</UL>
<UL>2. the audiophile, "surface"-oriented, listening mode<BR>
- mainly interested in quality/ <font color=#c0000>Beschaffenheit</font><BR>
(How is the sound shaped? What does it consist of? What is the structure and timbral quality of the sound object?)
</UL><BR>

Here are two model for a sound collection serving the differing interests for listening in any of the two modes mentioned above:
<BR>
1. The <font size=+2 color=#c0000><a href="calendar.htm">SoundCalendar</a></font> is an easily accessible collection of sounds, which have been encountered and recorded during a voyage to Japan in the summer and autumn of 1996.<BR>
2. The <font size=+2 color=#c0000><a href="garden.htm">SoundGarden</a></font> is an attempt to provide Hi-Fidelity sounds for musicians and audio-gourmets. The sounds and file formats were  selected with no regard to pragmatic questions of transfer time or disk space consumption. I didn't sacrifice quality (44 kHz, 16 bit) for convenience. Yet I tried to keep the sounds of the SoundGarden as short as possible. Think of the sounds of the SoundGarden as a collection of "bonzai" sound objects!<BR><BR>
<a href="garden.htm"><img src="ginfo/glogog.gif" border="0"></a><BR><BR>

The SoundCalendar and the SoundGarden refer to two different modes of listening, just as a MacDonald's and a French cuisine restaurant refer to different modes of eating. With its advantages and disadvantages each.<BR>
You will be served faster at MacDonald's, but .....

</BODY>
</HTML>
</DOC>
