<head>
<title>Antitrust Practice</title>
</head>
</HEADER><body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">
<center><img src="/gif/k-s2b.gif"><p>
<p>
<h1>Antitrust Practice</h1>
<HR><p>
</center>
<p>
King & Spalding's Antitrust Practice Group provides advice and assistance on all aspects of trade regulation and competition law. Clients' industries have ranged from services (including telecommunications, health care, and finance) to industrial goods (including chemicals, paper, and farm equipment) to consumer products (including foods, pharmaceuticals, and publications).
<P>
The Group handles the full range of antitrust issues, including mergers, competitor collaboration, distribution practices, and government investigations. 
<P><BR>
<STRONG>Mergers</STRONG><BR>
The Antitrust Practice Group provides advice on regulatory strategy, assists in structuring transactions to reduce legal risk, handles premerger filings with government enforcement agencies and ensuing investigations, and consults with the Firm's Corporate Practice Group on transaction documentation. Our lawyers have litigated merger cases before both trial courts and appellate courts. In addition to advising parties to transactions, the Group also advises the investment community.
<P>
<STRONG>Competitor Collaboration </STRONG><BR>
The Antitrust Practice Group represents clients in connection with investigations into unlawful conduct, such as price-fixing and market allocation. The Group acts for clients in grand jury proceedings, and our lawyers have conducted jury trials in criminal cases. 
<P>
The Group advises clients on numerous forms of legitimate competitor collaboration, including joint ventures, licensing arrangements, benchmarking and standard-setting, and strategic alliances. The Group also represents trade associations and similar organizations of competitors.
<P>
<STRONG>Distribution Practices</STRONG><BR>
The Antitrust Practice Group advises clients on issues relating to pricing, marketing, advertising, and related matters. The Group assists clients in developing pricing structures that adhere to legal prohibitions on price discrimination, resale price maintenance, and predatory pricing. Lawyers in the Group provide assistance to clients in developing marketing and advertising programs that adhere to legal restrictions on false or deceptive claims, discriminatory allowances, tying and bundling of products, exclusive dealing, customer and territorial limitations, and refusals to deal. The Group reviews promotional programs, distribution agreements, and similar client materials.
<P>
<STRONG>Other Matters</STRONG><BR>
The Antitrust Practice Group handles various other matters that arise under the trade regulation and competition laws. The Group develops compliance programs for clients and conducts antitrust audits of client organizations. It also advises clients with respect to state unfair competition statutes and common law, as well as with certain foreign laws.
<P>   
King & Spalding's Antitrust Practice Group works closely with numerous other components of the Firm. In particular, its lawyers collaborate on complex transactions with members of the Corporate, Intellectual Property, and Real Estate Practice Groups. Its lawyers also work with the Firm's Special Matters Group on criminal investigations into antitrust violations and with the Healthcare Practice Group on hospital mergers and physician networks.
<P>
For additional information regarding this practice area, contact:<br>
Kevin R. Sullivan (202) 626-2624<br>
William Blumenthal (202) 626-2625<p>
<hr>
<p>
<h4>Partners/Counsel in the Antitrust Practice:</h4>
