<html>
<head>
<title>International Practice</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<center><img src="/gif/k-s2b.gif"><p>
<h1>International Practice</h1>
<HR><p>
</center>
<p>
	The international legal work of King & Spalding is a substantial and rapidly-expanding part of its overall practice. In addition to representing U.S. clients in a wide variety of undertakings outside the United States, the Firm represents numerous non-U.S. clients as to their U.S. legal affairs.  These clients include companies, government agencies and natural persons from throughout the world.
<P>
	<STRONG>Foreign Investment in the United States</STRONG>.  King & Spalding advises a large number of private and institutional foreign investors as to various types of investments throughout the United States. The Firm has represented foreign clients in acquisitions of numerous U.S. corporations and has done a significant amount of work in structuring funds for foreign investment in the United States. The Firm also does a substantial amount of international licensing, distribution and franchising work.
<P>
	<STRONG>U.S. Investment Abroad</STRONG>.  King & Spalding advises a growing number of U.S. clients with respect to their overseas investments and business activities. The Firm has been involved in a wide variety of international corporate, commercial and financial transactions for such clients, including structuring, negotiating and effecting international joint ventures and strategic alliances, cross border acquisitions, international license, distribution and franchising arrangements and international financial arrangements including "double-dip" lease transactions and other tax-advantaged financings.
<P>
	The Firm has particular experience in accessing finance and political risk insurance support from international financial institutions such as the International Finance Corporation, the Overseas Private Investment Corporation, and U.S. Eximbank. A number of the Firm's partners have long-standing experience with European business transactions, and three of its partners were born in Europe and received their original legal training there. Recently the Firm has become increasingly active in business transactions for U.S. clients in the Far East, Latin America and the Commonwealth of Independent States. The Firm has been particularly active in China, where it has assisted U.S. companies in the establishment of business operations since the late 1970s.
<P>
	<STRONG>International Joint Ventures and Strategic Alliances</STRONG>.  King & Spalding has a substantial practice involving international joint ventures and strategic alliances. This representation includes assistance in the creation of large telecommunications joint ventures in Europe, Latin America and the Far East. The Firm recently assisted a client in the establishment of China s first joint venture for the manufacture of cable television equipment.
<P>
	<STRONG>International Investment Funds</STRONG>.  King & Spalding has extensive experience in representing sponsors of international investment funds, including funds offered privately to non-U.S. investors for investment in the United States and funds offered privately to U.S. investors for investment outside the United States. Such funds have invested in venture capital situations, leveraged buyouts, publicly and privately traded securities portfolios, and real estate. The Firm s fund sponsor clients have included German merchant banks, Dutch real estate and venture capital fund sponsors and managers, a consortium of European venture capitalists and several Kuwaiti merchant and investment banks, as well as U.S. investment banks.
<P>
	<STRONG>International Finance Practice</STRONG>.  The 1992 merger into King & Spalding of the New York firm of Porter & Travers significantly enhanced King & Spalding s international financing capabilities with the addition of an established, integrated practice group having an industry-wide reputation in the areas of complex structured financing transactions and the development of new financial products. The New York-based group has substantial experience in cross-border financings of all types, including, in particular, project financings, LDC debt swaps, debt repurchase transactions and trade finance. The group s clients include numerous non-U.S. banks.
<P>
	In particular, the financing partners in the New York office are recognized as being among the leaders in the development of the project finance model successfully utilized by the cogeneration, independent power and alternate-energy industries. The group s work in this area, combined with its extensive international experience, has led to an expanding practice advising both U.S. and non-U.S. developers in the development of infrastructure and other projects overseas, as well as advising governmental agencies in their privatization initiatives.
<P>
	<STRONG>International Trade Regulation and Customs Practice</STRONG>.  Lawyers in this practice handle a broad range of international trade regulatory and legislative matters. They practice before the U.S. Congress, the Office of the U.S. Trade Representative, the U.S. Department of Commerce, the U.S. International Trade Commission, the U.S. Customs Service, the U.S. Court of International Trade, and various other governmental and administrative bodies.  Together, they have extensive experience in antidumping, countervailing duty, and other international trade and customs matters.
<P>
	King & Spalding's trade lawyers are part of the Firm's Litigation Group and have broad experience in civil litigation. They are trained in developing the factual record and legal theories that are most likely to result in a favorable outcome to the client. This litigation experience, not shared by many trade lawyers, gives the Firm an advantage in handling trade remedy litigation before the U.S. International Trade Commission and the Department of Commerce.
<P>
<STRONG>Kuwaiti Practice</STRONG>.  King & Spalding has a substantial practice involving representation of Kuwaiti institutions and individuals as to their investments and other affairs in the United States and advises a number of U.S. clients with respect to their business activities in Kuwait. 
<P>
	<STRONG>Tax Aspects of the International Practice</STRONG>.  Lawyers involved in the Firm s International Practice frequently focus on international legal and tax planning and the establishment of multinational tax and legal structures. Lawyers from the Firm s Tax Department are often involved in the tax aspects of such international transactions.
<P>
	<STRONG>Political Emergency Protective Structures.</STRONG>  Lawyers in the Firm have worked extensively on "failsafe" legal structures aimed at protecting U.S. and other international investments of foreign clients against the adverse effects of possible political emergencies in their home countries and against the adverse effects of actions the U.S. Government might take under the Trading with the Enemy Act and related laws. The Firm has worked on such protective structures for a variety of clients, including non-U.S. families and private and publicly-owned European and Middle Eastern companies.
<P>
<STRONG>1996 Olympics</STRONG>.  King & Spalding is general counsel for the Atlanta Committee for the Olympic Games ("ACOG"), the legal entity that will conduct the 1996 Summer Olympics. The Firm represents ACOG in a wide range of international matters, including licensing, trademark protection and contracting as to television broadcast rights.
<P>
	<STRONG>Foreign Languages</STRONG>.  Various lawyers in the Firm speak one or more of the following languages, in addition to English: Danish, French, German, Japanese, Norwegian, Russian, Spanish and Swedish.
<hr>
<p>
For additional information about this practice area, contact:<br>
W. Donald Knight, Jr. (404) 572-4764<p>
<HR><P><H4>Partners & Counsel in the International Practice:</H4>
<a href="/htm/knight.htm"> W. Donald Knight, Jr.</A><BR>
<A HREF="http:/htm/busbee.htm">George D. Busbee</A>
