<head>
<title>Banking & Finance Practice</title>
<meta name="CreatedBy" content="WP Internet Publisher 6.1">
</head>
<body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<center><img src="/gif/k-s2b.gif"><p>
<h1>Banking &amp; Finance Practice</h1>
<P><HR><p>
</center>
<p>
The Firm maintains two groups engaged in the banking and finance practice: one in its Atlanta office and the other in its New York office.  Both practice groups provide services in connection with private finance and other commercial transactions, including secured and unsecured credit facilities; asset-based financings; project and other structured financings; leveraged leases; venture and mezzanine investments; a wide array of real estate financings; private placements of debt securities; highly leveraged transactions; interest rate swaps, currency swaps and other hedge transactions and derivatives; collateralized mortgage obligations; asset securitization; participations and syndications; trade finance; LDC debt swaps and funds; and credit enhanced transactions.  The groups have substantial experience in workouts and restructurings, and combine both borrower and lender experience.  The groups also provide services in connection with acquisitions of banks and thrift institutions, as well as bank and thrift regulatory issues.
<P>
These practice groups represent a number of money center banks; foreign banks; large regional bank holding companies and banks; smaller local financial institutions; insurance holding companies and insurance companies; leasing and finance companies; other large financial institutions; governmental or quasi-governmental organizations; and major finance subsidiaries of multinational and national corporations.<p>

For additional information regarding this practice area, contact:<br>
Albert H. Conrad, Jr. (404) 572-4807<br>
Peter K.Storey (212) 556-2170<p>
