<head>
<title>Bankruptcy & Commercial Litigation</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<center><img src="/gif/k-s2b.gif"><p>
<h1>Bankruptcy &amp; Commercial Litigation</h1>
<HR><p>
</center>
<p>
King & Spalding's Bankruptcy and Commercial Litigation Group reflects the Firm's commitment to anticipating and serving its clients  needs.  King & Spalding has long been established as a leader in the field of creditor representation with an emphasis on the representation of financial institutions.  The Bankruptcy and Commercial Litigation Group provides valuable knowledge and experience in the areas of commercial debt restructuring, workouts, bankruptcy and creditors  rights litigation. 
<P>
Typical activity for the Bankruptcy and Commercial Litigation Group includes out-of-court debt restructuring and workouts; dealing with problem real estate and asset-based commercial loans; negotiating and litigating over the terms of debtor-in-possession financing, use of cash collateral, adequate protection and relief from automatic stay; purchasing assets from businesses on the verge of or in Chapter 11; acquiring companies through Chapter 11; negotiating and litigating over preference, fraudulent conveyance and other avoidance actions; and drafting and confirming creditors' Chapter 11 plans.  In these activities, King & Spalding's bankruptcy lawyers have worked closely with other practice groups in the Firm including Commercial, Banking and Finance, Real Estate, Tax, Corporate, Environmental, and Labor.  In addition, the Firm's familiarity with, and experience in, mezzanine financings and venture investments, technology-based corporate financings, leasing, project financings and structured financings have enabled it to play an important role in the structuring of innovative workout solutions.
<P>
Our representations involve regular lending and business clients of the Firm as well as creditors and prospective purchasers who call upon the Firm because of a particular expertise or geographic location.
<P>
For additional information about this practice area, contact:<br>
James A. Pardo, Jr. (404) 572-4794<p>
<hr>
<p>
<h4>Partners/Counsel in the Bankruptcy and Commercial Litigation Practice:</h4>
<a href="/htm/epstein.htm">David G. Epstein</a><br>
