<head>
<title>Labor, ERISA & Employment Practice</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<center><img src="/gif/k-s2b.gif"><p>
<h1>Labor, ERISA &amp; Employment Practice</h1>
<HR><p>
</center>
<p>
King &amp; Spalding represents employers in labor relations, equal employment
opportunity ("EEO"), ERISA, and other employment related matters.  The Firm's labor, ERISA and employment law activities are handled primarily by sixteen attorneys, three ERISA coordinators, and three experienced paralegals.  <p>

This Group represents employers directly in their relationships with labor unions, before the National Labor Relations Board and in administrative proceedings and litigation over union organizational campaigns, elections, unfair labor practice proceedings, collective bargaining negotiations, arbitrations, and various types of work stoppages.<p>

Attorneys in this Group represent employers in state and federal trial and appellate courts and before administrative agencies such as the Equal Employment Opportunity Commission, the U.S. Department of Labor's Office of Federal Contract Compliance Programs, and state fair employment practices commissions.  The Group handles discrimination charges, investigations arising from those charges, and litigation involving claims based on race, sex, religion, national origin, age, handicap and veterans  rights laws and regulations.  The Group has considerable experience in complex EEO litigation and jury trials.  In addition, the Group conducts a wide range of compliance training programs and assists employers in the development and audit of affirmative action plans, as well as with OFCCP compliance reviews, "show cause" notices and debarment proceedings.<p>

Labor, ERISA and employment lawyers advise employers on the design, preparation, communication, administration and operation of all forms of employee benefit plans and executive compensation programs and the related funding vehicles, including pension and profit sharing plans, 401(k) plans, leveraged ESOPs, stock option plans, incentive compensation programs, "cafeteria" plans, VEBAs, and on all mergers and acquisitions and other business transactions which involve such plans and programs.  The Firm also represents clients involved in ERISA-related controversies in federal and state courts and before the Internal Revenue Service, the U.S. Department of Labor and the Pension Benefit Guaranty Corporation. <p>

This Group is experienced in representing clients with respect to various labor standards laws, including wage-hour (including Fair Labor Standards, Walsh-Healey, Davis-Bacon, Service Contract, and Contract Work Hours and Safety Standards Acts), occupational safety and health, workers compensation, unemployment compensation, and related matters.<p>

Attorneys from this Group conduct various training programs for its clients, including a comprehensive employment law program and specific programs on such subjects as union avoidance, equal employment opportunity, drug and alcohol testing programs, and compensation and employee benefits administration.<p>

For additional information about this practice area, contact:<br>
Donald S. Kohla (404) 572-4926<p>
<hr>
<p>
