<head>
<title>Construction & Developement Practice</title>
<meta name="CreatedBy" content="WP Internet Publisher 6.1">
</head>
<body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<center><img src="/gif/k-s2b.gif"><p>
<h1>Construction &amp; Development Practice</h1>
<HR><p>
</center>
<p>
King & Spalding offers a complete range of legal services for domestic and foreign clients engaged in construction and development activities in the United States and abroad.  These services include counseling and contract drafting during the financing, design and construction process, with a view toward avoiding claims and disputes, and mediation, arbitration or litigation of claims and disputes that arise out of the development and construction process.  The Construction and Development Practice also works closely with the Firm's Project Finance Group in the review and structuring of construction and development contracts consistent with the dictates of the financial community. The Firm also represents internationally known banking and business institutions concerning the financing and development of a variety of projects, including utilities and cogeneration plants.
<P>
The Firm is general counsel to the Atlanta Committee for the Olympic Games (ACOG), host of the 1996 Summer Olympic Games, which involves a massive construction and development effort.  In its capacity as general counsel, King & Spalding has performed legal work in connection with a wide variety of ACOG's activities, including the development, design and construction of Olympic venues.
<P>For additional information about this practice area, contact:<br>
John W. Hinchey (404) 572-4922<p>
<p>
<hr>
<p>
<h4>Partners/Counsel in the Construction &amp; Development Practice:</h4>
<a href="/htm/hinchey.htm">John W. Hinchey</a><br>
<a href="/htm/codner.htm">Fred G. Codner</a><p>
<p>
