<head>
<title>Litigation Practice</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<center><img src="/gif/k-s2b.gif"><p>
<h1>Litigation Practice</h1>
<HR><p>
</center>
<p>
King &amp; Spalding's Litigation Practice includes representation of clients in civil and criminal matters in both state and federal courts throughout the nation. Over 100 lawyers in the Firm, including former United States Attorney General <a href="/htm/bell.htm">Griffin Bell</a>, are actively engaged in the litigation practice. Nine of its senior trial lawyers are fellows of The American College of Trial lawyers. <p>

King &amp; Spalding's Litigation Practice includes the following practice groups: <p>
<b><A HREF="/menu/comlit.htm">Commercial</A>. </b>Lawyers in this group represent clients in commercial disputes of all types, including contract disputes, business torts, securities litigation, shareholder class actions and derivative suits, banking fraud, RICO, antitrust litigation and professional liability claims.<p>

<a href="/menu/prodliab.htm"><STRONG>Product Liability</STRONG></a>.This group represents automotive manufacturers, drug manufacturing companies, tobacco companies, and other clients in major product liability matters in local, regional and national litigation. <p>

<b><a href="/menu/special.htm">Special Matters</a></b>. Services rendered by lawyers in this group include representation in criminal or regulatory investigations; representation of businesses that have been victimized by dishonest employees, vendors or others; and representation of corporations and corporate officers against charges such as bank fraud in criminal or related shareholder derivative litigation. The group has represented insurance companies, financial institutions and government contractors. The Special Matters Group, headed by former U.S. Attorney General <a href="/htm/bell.htm">Griffin Bell</a>, includes former U.S. Attorney <a href="/htm/thompson.htm">Larry Thompson</a>; former Chief, Fraud Section of the Department of Justice's Criminal Division, <a href="/htm/hendrick.htm">William Hendricks</a>; <A HREF="/htm/sollers.htm">J. Sedwick Sollers III</A>, former Assistant U.S. Attorney; and <A HREF="/htm/duffey.htm">William S. Duffey, Jr.</A>, former Deputy Independent Counsel of the Whitewater Investigation. <p>

<b><a href="/menu/itrc.htm">International Trade Regulation and Customs</a>. </b>This group prosecutes and defends international trade remedy actions (e.g., antidumping cases) before the U.S. International Trade Commission, the U.S. Department of Commerce, the Office of the U.S. Trade Representative, and the U.S. Court of International Trade. Customs protests and related litigation involving tariff classification and other customs issues are handled
on behalf of U.S. importers.<p>

<b><a href="/menu/bankrupt.htm">Bankruptcy</a>. </b>This practice involves the representation of clients in bankruptcy and related litigation, including litigation growing out of troubled transactions. <p>

<b><a href="/menu/ipt.htm">Intellectual Property and Technology</a>. </b>These lawyers represent clients in disputes and litigation arising out of the creation, acquisition, protection or licensing of a wide variety of technology and intellectual property rights, including patents, trademarks, copyrights, trade secrets, and rights under license agreements and other technical contracts. There are numerous lawyers who regularly litigate to enforce, protect and resolve claims involving intellectual property rights. The Firm has an active counseling practice involving all aspects of intellectual property which supports the Litigation Group in litigated matters. <p>

<b><a href="/menu/envir.htm">Environmental</a> and <a href="/menu/toxic.htm">Toxic Tort</a>.</b> These groups handle a wide variety of environmental and toxic tort litigation, ranging from Superfund litigation to personal injury claims based on exposure to alleged toxic substances. The Environmental Practice provides valuable experience in the substantive laws and regulations, as well as knowledge of the medical and scientific issues involved in these cases. The Litigation Group provides the trial expertise required to handle the litigation.<p>

<b><a href="/menu/labor.htm">Labor, ERISA and Employment Law</a>.</b> The lawyers in this pratice group handle employment and labor disputes, including employment discrimination claims, wrongful discharge suits, ERISA litigation, and traditional labor disputes. <p>

<A HREF="/menu/support.htm"><STRONG>Litigation Support</STRONG></A>.
King & Spalding has long recognized the power of technology to improve its lawyers' productivity while greatly reducing clients' litigation costs.  In 1993 King & Spalding made a substantial capital investment in document imaging technology and established an in-house Litigation Support Department to better serve its clients. King & Spalding is dedicated to remaining at the cutting edge of technology in order to serve its clients more efficiently and effectively.
<P>
For additional information about this practice area, contact:<br>
Charles M. Shaffer, Jr. (404) 572-4785<p>
<p>
<p>
<center><HR><p>
</center><center><A HREF="http:/default.htm"><IMG SRC="/gif/hp.gif" ALT="[Home Page]"></A> <A HREF="http:/menu/groups.htm"><IMG SRC="/gif/pg.gif" ALT="[Practice Groups]"></A> <A HREF="http:/menu/attorn.htm"><IMG SRC="/gif/atty.gif" alt="[Attorneys]"></A><br><A HREF="http:/menu/articles.htm"><IMG SRC="/gif/art1.gif" alt="[Articles]"></A> <A HREF="http:/menu/leglink.htm"><IMG SRC="/gif/lr.gif" alt="[Legal Resources]"></A> <A HREF="http:/menu/recruit.htm"><IMG SRC="/gif/recruit.jpg" ALT="Recruiting"></A></center>
