<HEAD>
<TITLE> Electric Utility Industry Financing Practice</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER>
<img src="/gif/k-s2b.gif"><p>
<H1>Electric Utility Industry Financing Practice </H1><P>
<HR></CENTER>
<P>
King & Spalding offers extensive experience in representing lenders and other investors in connection with a broad range of financings provided to the electric utility industry. King & Spalding attorneys have unique experience in advising clients on the regulatory, financial, commercial and legal aspects of debt and equity investments in all segments of the electric utility business, including regulated, investor-owned utilities, regulated and unregulated utility holding companies, foreign power investments and unregulated power production affiliates of electric utilities.
<P>
Lawyers in the Firm's Banking and Finance Practice are very active in the representation of foreign and domestic money center banks in connection with the structuring, syndication and documentation of a broad range of financial products utilized by the utility industry. Typical transactions include secured and unsecured term and revolving credit facilities, credit-enhanced transactions for taxable and tax-exempt bond and commercial paper programs, nuclear fuel and other lease financings, derivatives, foreign and domestic acquisition facilities and debt restructurings. Banking and Finance Practice lawyers active in the utility lending practice are supported by their colleagues at the Firm who are experienced in bankruptcy, securities and capital markets, federal and state utility regulatory matters, environmental law, public finance and litigation. In addition, many of the lawyers most active in the electric utility financing practice also have extensive experience in the project financing of independent power facilities, and thus offer an in-depth understanding of the competitive forces currently affecting the electric utility industry.
<P>
For additional information about this practice area, contact:<BR>
Peter K. Storey (212) 556-2170<P>

<center><HR><p><A HREF="http:/default.htm"><IMG SRC="/gif/hp.gif" ALT="[Home Page]"></A> <A HREF="http:/menu/groups.htm"><IMG SRC="/gif/pg.gif" ALT="[Practice Groups]"></A> <A HREF="http:/menu/attorn.htm"><IMG SRC="/gif/atty.gif" alt="[Attorneys]"></A><br><A HREF="http:/menu/articles.htm"><IMG SRC="/gif/art1.gif" alt="[Articles]"></A> <A HREF="http:/menu/leglink.htm"><IMG SRC="/gif/lr.gif" alt="[Legal Resources]"></A> <A HREF="http:/menu/recruit.htm"><IMG SRC="/gif/recruit.jpg" ALT="Recruiting"></A></center></BODY>
