<head>
<title>Public Finance Practice</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<center><img src="/gif/k-s2b.gif"><p>
<h1>Public Finance Practice</h1>
<HR><p>
</center>
<p>
King &amp; Spalding has been nationally recognized in government financings for more than 60 years.  King &amp; Spalding was the first firm in the southeastern United States to be listed in the <i>Red Book</i>, the official directory for bond counsel whose legal opinions are nationally recognized by major purchasers or underwriters of municipal bonds.  The Firm has continuously maintained a Public Finance Practice to handle tax-exempt financings since the 1930s.  <p>

The Public Finance Practice serves as bond counsel in connection with borrowings by states, counties, cities and public authorities throughout the United States.  King &amp; Spalding has acted as bond counsel for virtually all of the cities and counties within the State of Georgia and has also acted as bond counsel in 39 other states.  <p>

Since the 1960s, the Public Finance Practice has also been active in the area of private activity bonds, working on a variety of financings for utilities, manufacturing facilities, airports, docks, ports, multi-family housing projects, sports facilities, hospitals and convention facilities.  In the municipal bond industry rankings published by the <i>Red Book</i>, King &amp; Spalding ranks 25th among the top 100 bond counsel nationwide and first in the State of Georgia.  <p>

The Public Finance Practice also acts as counsel to underwriters of tax-exempt borrowings and prepares official statements and underwriting agreements in connection with the public sale and distribution of tax-exempt obligations.  King &amp; Spalding served as underwriter's counsel on a larger number of issues, and on a larger dollar volume of issues, than any other firm based in Georgia according to statistics compiled by the <i>Red Book</i>.<p>

The Public Finance Practice's practice includes underwriter's counsel representation on virtually every type of public finance issue, and for both regional and national underwriting firms.  The Public Finance Practice also serves as counsel to placement agents, trustees, letter of credit issuers, remarketing agents and industrial concerns entitled to use tax-exempt financing.  <p>

For additional information about this practice area, contact:<br>
Robert L. Steed (404) 572-4656<p>
<hr>
<p>
