<head>
<title>Real Estate Practice</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<center><img src="/gif/k-s2b.gif"><p>
<h1>Real Estate Practice</h1>
<HR><p>
</center>
<p>
King & Spalding's Real Estate Group provides advice and counsel to clients in all aspects of the commercial real estate industry.  The Firm represents developers, investors, lenders, owners and underwriters of real estate.  Approximately 25 lawyers in the Firm's Atlanta and New York offices are actively engaged in this Practice.
<P>
The Firm has one of the leading Real Estate Securitization Practices in the United States, serving as both issuer's and underwriters' counsel in numerous transactions over the last four years.  The Real Estate Group is supported in this area by the Firm's Corporate, Tax, Environmental, and ERISA Practices.
<P>
The Firm's Developer Practice includes active involvement in the planning, acquisition, leasing, financing, construction and management of office buildings, shopping centers, hotels, apartments, multiple use developments, industrial and business parks, including build-to-suit for lease or sale transactions.  Involvement includes developments throughout the United States on behalf of U.S. and foreign based developers.  The Practice includes extensive work in partnerships and the growing governmental regulatory requirements related to zoning, land use planning, environmental safety, wetlands regulations and historic preservation.  The Real Estate Group is supported in this area by the Firm's Tax, Environmental and Corporate Practices.
<P>
Lender and investor representation includes U.S. and foreign banks, pension funds, credit companies, insurance companies and individuals in lending and investment transactions throughout the country.  This Practice has involved various forms of financings, joint ventures, debt instruments convertible to equity ownership, and similar arrangements related to sophisticated real estate transactions, including significant experience in the representation of non-U.S. investors in U.S. real estate.  The Practice is supported in this area by its Tax and Corporate attorneys.
<P>
The Group has extensive experience in the restructuring or "workout" of loan and equity transactions and is supported by the Firm's Commercial, Bankruptcy and Commercial Litigation lawyers.
<P>
The Real Estate Group also counsels Firm clients who are not in the real estate business, but become involved in real estate transactions and issues regarding property in normal business activities, including merger and acquisition transactions.<p>
<P>
For additional information about this practice area, contact:<br>
David L. Coker (404) 572-4918<br>
Mason W. Stephenson (404) 572-4945<p>
