<head>
<title>Securities and Shareholder Litigation Practice</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<center><img src="/gif/k-s2b.gif"><p>
<h1>Securities and Shareholder Litigation Practice</h1>
<HR><p>
</center>
<p>
King & Spalding has kept pace with the steady growth of securities and shareholder litigation over the last decade by continuing to expand its practice in this area.  As a result, the Firm has acquired substantial and varied experience in defending litigation and conducting investigations arising out of allegations of securities fraud or breach of fiduciary duties. 
<P>
King & Spalding's clients in securities and shareholder litigation matters have included outside directors, inside officers and directors, corporations, and board committees such as special litigation committees and committees of independent directors in transactional litigation.  Although most of the Firm's work in this area is defense-oriented, King & Spalding has also represented acquiring companies in takeover battles and tender offer litigation.  In addition, the Firm has both defended and prosecuted shareholder derivative actions and other litigation by minority shareholders. 
<P>
The breadth of the Firm's representation in this area enables the Firm to provide its clients with experienced lawyers who are very familiar with tested and successful legal strategies in defending claims of securities fraud and breach of fiduciary duties.  The Firm has also worked closely with a number of the leading expert economists whose testimony is vital to a strong defense of these actions.  The Firm's attorneys are particularly experienced in dealing with the complexities associated with the defense of parallel civil litigation and governmental/criminal investigations.
<P>
<STRONG>Representative Securities and Shareholder Litigation Matters</STRONG>
<P>
King & Spalding's Securities and Shareholder Litigation Practice has included a broad range of litigation and/or investigations concerning securities offerings; compliance with financial accounting standards; mergers and acquisitions; tender offers; proxy contests; and claims of insider trading.  <P>
While the Firm's representation in this practice area is centered in the Southeast, King & Spalding has represented clients in a number of securities/shareholder litigation matters in New York, Delaware, Illinois, Washington, D.C., and California.  Representative securities/shareholder litigation matters in which the Firm's attorneys have been involved include the following:
<P>
<UL>
<LI>Defense of a public REIT and certain of its trustees and officers in litigation seeking to enjoin a merger with a non-public affiliated REIT.<P>
<LI>Defense of a large retail sales company and certain of its directors and officers in securities fraud suits, a shareholder derivative action, and parallel grand jury and SEC investigations.<P>
<LI>Defense of inside officers and directors against securities fraud and breach of fiduciary duties claims in four separate civil actions involving one of the nation's largest bank failures. <P>
<LI>Representation of the Independent Litigation Committee of the Board of Directors of a large oil company in connection with the shareholder litigation.<P>
<LI>Defense of a large public accounting firm against allegations of securities fraud based on the client's role in the preparation of a partnership prospectus and financial audits.<P>
<LI>Defense of a major computer software company in a securities fraud class action alleging accounts receivables and inventory manipulation and noncompliance with financial accounting rules.<P>
<LI>Defense of a provider of health care services against allegations of securities fraud and breach of fiduciary duties under ERISA.<P>
<LI>Defense of the outside directors of a Midwest-based defense contractor in shareholder litigation and related investigations arising out of the company's agreement to plead guilty to charges of defrauding the U.S. Government.<P>
<LI>Defense of the outside directors of a major Southeast-based utility company in shareholder litigation arising out of cost overruns in the construction of a nuclear power plant.<P>
<LI>Representation of a Southeast-based bank holding company in connection with an SEC investigation.<P>
<LI>Defense of a Fortune 100 company in minority shareholder litigation challenging proxy statement disclosures involving business transactions with a partially-owned subsidiary.
</UL>
<P>
For additional information, contact:<br>
Joseph B. Haynes (404) 572-4792<p>

