<head>
<title>Tax Practice</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<center><img src="/gif/k-s2b.gif"><p>
<h1>Tax Practice</h1>
<HR><p>
</center>
<p>

King &amp; Spalding's Tax Practice includes structuring of both domestic and foreign business organizations and transactions, representing taxpayers' interests in the tax legislative and regulatory processes, and representing taxpayers in government audits and tax litigation.  The Firm also handles all types of Georgia state and local tax matters. <p>

Numerous King &amp; Spalding tax lawyers have held significant tax policy positions in the Internal Revenue Service, Treasury Department and the Congress.  Harry L. Gutman was Chief of Staff of the Joint Committee on Taxation of the United States Congress from 1991 through December, 1993, and also served as Deputy Tax Legislative Counsel in the Treasury Department during the Carter Administration.  Abraham N.M. Shashy was Chief Counsel of the Internal Revenue Service from February, 1990, through January, 1993, and William F. Nelson was Chief Counsel of the Internal Revenue Service from August, 1986, through October, 1988.  William S. McKee and Robert G. Woodward each served as Tax Legislative Counsel in the Treasury Department during the Reagan Administration.  Messrs. McKee and Nelson are co-authors of a multi-volume treatise, <i>Federal Taxation of Partnerships and Partners, </i>that is generally regarded as the leading commentary on partnership tax issues. <p>

Other King &amp; Spalding tax partners who have significant government experience include Steven R. Lainoff, who served as Associate Chief Counsel (International) at the IRS and International Tax Counsel at the Treasury Department (the two highest positions for international tax lawyers in the federal government); Thomas F. Wessel, who was Special Counsel to the Chief Counsel at the IRS and Associate Tax Legislative Counsel at the Treasury; Jackie S. Levinson, former Deputy Tax Legislative Counsel at the Treasury; Mark A. Kuller, former Special Assistant to the Chief Counsel, IRS and Attorney-Advisor in the Treasury's Office of Tax Legislative Counsel; James H. Lokey, Jr., former Associate Tax Legislative Counsel at the Treasury; Susan Jewett, former Attorney-Advisor in the Treasury's Office of Tax Legislative Counsel; and Sandra Hallmark, former Attorney-Advisor in the IRS Office of Chief Counsel.<p>

For additional information about this practice area, contact:<br>
Robert G. Woodward (404) 572-3353<br>
William S. McKee (202) 626-2908<p>
<hr>
