<head>
<title>Toxic Tort Practice</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<center><img src="/gif/k-s2b.gif"><p>
<h1>Toxic Tort Practice</h1>
<HR><p>
</center>
<p>
The Toxic Tort Practice at King &amp; Spalding includes representation of major
manufacturers in the following industries: chemical, pharmaceutical, pulp and paper, herbicide and pesticide, automotive, petroleum, capacitor manufacturing, railroad tank car manufacturing, hazardous waste disposal and others.<p>

The Firm has been heavily involved in PCB and dioxin litigation, including major class action representation.  In addition, the Firm has been involved in a variety of chemical substances cases such as asbestos, formaldehyde, solvents (such as TCE), petroleum products, pesticides, methane, hydrogen sulfide and other chemicals.<p>

Our toxic tort litigation has involved individual claims, class actions, and multiple claims under various types of case management orders.  The claims have been brought by workers, surrounding property owners, riparian owners, and product end-users.  Exposure claims have involved air, water, soil, food, and other routes of exposure.  Injury claims have included personal illnesses (including immune system impairment), fear, increased risk of disease, property damage and business losses. <P>

Equally important, the Toxic Tort Practice has afforded us the opportunity to work closely with leading experts throughout the country in a variety of disciplines including toxicology, epidemiology, immunology, neurology, psychiatry, oncology, teratology, risk assessment, chemistry, hydrology, geology, aquatics, waste water treatment, air dispersion modeling, and many more.  Similarly, we have come up against many of the familiar plaintiffs' experts in toxic tort cases, including those who espouse "theories" of
clinical ecology, chemical AIDS, "one-hit" causation, multiple chemical sensitivity and others. <p>
<P>
For further information about this practice area, contact:<br>
J. Kevin Buster (404) 572-4804<br>
<hr>
<p>
<h4>Partners/Counsel in the Toxic Tort Practice:</h4>
<a href="/htm/partain.htm">Eugene G. Partain</a><br>
<a href="/htm/leake.htm">Nolan C. Leake</a><br>
<a href="/htm/buster.htm">J. Kevin Buster</a><br>
<a href="/htm/toledo.htm">Carmen R. Toledo</a><br>
