<head>
<title>Insurance Practice</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<center><img src="/gif/k-s2b.gif"><p>
<h1>Insurance Practice</h1>
<HR><p>
</center>
<p>
King & Spalding represents numerous insurance industry clients in connection with merger and acquisition transactions, corporate and securities matters, regulatory issues and litigation matters.
<P>
<STRONG>Corporate, Securities and Regulatory Matters</STRONG>
<P>
The Firm assists with the strategic, transactional and regulatory aspects of insurance company acquisitions.  The insurance company acquisition transactions the Firm has handled for clients include public exchange offers, public tender offers, private mergers and stock sales and private asset transfers.
<P>
The Firm has extensive experience in representing acquiring companies in connection with state insurance commissioner change of control hearings.  The Firm also represents an insurance company in connection with the purchase of a target insurance company subject to a state insurance commissioner rehabilitation procedure.
<P>
As corporate counsel to a number of insurance companies, the Firm has been involved in real estate, tax, ERISA, and securities matters.  The Firm has assisted insurance company clients in the public offering and private placement of common stock, preferred stock and debentures.  In addition to this issuer representation, the Firm has represented underwriters in connection with public offerings by long-term care, supplemental accidental and health and automobile insurers.  The Firm has also represented insurance clients involved with the sale of tax-qualified annuities.
<P>
The Firm has been engaged in connection with Georgia regulatory matters involving admission of insurers, approval of policy forms, interpretation of policy provisions and investigation and termination of insurance agency relationships.  The Firm has also been actively involved in the analysis of corporate, securities, tax and regulatory issues relating to demutualization transactions.
<P>
The Firm has extensive experience in the representation of insurance actuary firms, including analysis of demutualizations, acquisitions, software licensing and new product design.  
<P>
<STRONG>Litigation Matters</STRONG>
<P>
In the area of litigation, the Firm has represented insurance companies in class action cases involving illegal rate charges and violations of agency agreements, in breach of contract cases, in antitrust matters, malpractice suits and RICO claims, as well as hearings before numerous state insurance commissions.
<P>
For additional information regarding this practice area, contact:<br>
Nolan C. Leake (404) 572-4776<br>
Jon R. Harris, Jr. (404) 572-3324<p>

<center>
<HR>
