<HEADER>
<TITLE>Jill P. Anderson</TITLE>
</HEADER><body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>Jill P. Anderson</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/anderson.jpg">

Jill Anderson joined King & Spalding in 1987 and became counsel to
the Firm in 1995.  She practices in the Atlanta office in the Real Estate
Practice.
<P>
Ms. Anderson focuses on commercial real estate transactions including zoning and regulatory law, leasing law, and developer and lender representation in the acquisition, development, financing and sale of commercial properties.
<P>
A 1979 cum laude graduate of the journalism school of the University
of Georgia, Ms. Anderson earned her J.D., with honors, in 1987 from Emory
University, where she was also Executive Notes and Comments Editor of
the <EM>Emory Law Journal, </EM>and also was awarded the Order of the Coif.
She is a member of the State Bar of Georgia, the Atlanta Bar Association
and the American Bar Association.
<P>
<P>
<A HREF="/menu/real.htm">Real Estate Practice</A><P>
<p><center>
