<HTML>
<HEADER>
<TITLE>Scott J. Arnold</TITLE>
</HEADER><body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>Scott J. Arnold</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/arnolds.jpg">

Scott Arnold has been active since 1975 in the full range of commercial real estate issues. He represents, particularly, developers of large commercial properties and investors, both foreign and domestic, in properties throughout the U.S.
<P>
Those Atlanta-based projects in which Mr. Arnold has had primary or significant responsibility include a 1.1 million square foot downtown high-rise office tower, on behalf of its developer; a two million square foot mixed-use suburban project, on behalf of its developer; a 1.1 million square foot midtown high rise office tower, on behalf of its Japan-based purchaser; a 600,000 square foot high-rise office tower, on behalf of its Japan-based lender; and a prestigious hotel, on behalf of its developer and operator.
<P>
Mr. Arnold's practice, representing investors in commercial real estate, is national in scope. He has worked on prestigious commercial real estate projects from San Francisco to Manhattan to Atlanta. In addition, Mr. Arnold has had extensive experience on a worldwide basis in the luxury hotel sector.
<P>
He is a regular lecturer at professional seminars and continuing legal education functions and, in 1990, was elected to the American College of Real Estate Lawyers.
<P>
Mr. Arnold began his practice directly upon graduation from the University of Michigan Law School in 1975 (J.D., magna cum laude). He earned a B.A. in Economics from the University of Missouri in 1972, where he was also Phi Beta Kappa.
<P>
<P>
<A HREF="/menu/real.htm">Real Estate Practice</A><P>
