<TITLE>R. Byron Attridge</TITLE>
</HEADER><body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>R. Byron Attridge</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/attridge.jpg">

Byron Attridge has trial and appellate experience in federal and state courts throughout the country.  He has practiced in the United States Court of Appeals for the Fourth, Fifth, Eighth, and Eleventh Circuits, and the Supreme Court of the United States, as well as various federal district courts and local and appellate state courts.
<P>
His area of practice is general commercial litigation, including professional liability, environmental, security transactions, trademark, creditors rights and product liability.  Mr. Attridge served as Special Assistant Attorney for the State of Georgia from 1981-82.
<P>
Mr. Attridge is a Fellow of the American College of Trial Lawyers, currently serving on the Committee on Complex Litigation; Special Committee for Tort Reform (1989-90).  His past bar activities include service as a member of the Board of Governors of the State Bar of Georgia (1974-83), President of the Atlanta Bar Association (1971-72), and Chairman of the State Board of Bar Examiners (1984).
<P>
Mr. Attridge graduated from Princeton University in 1955 and received his law degree from Emory University School of Law in 1961.  He joined King & Spalding in 1960 and became a partner in 1965. <P>
<P>
