<HEADER>
<TITLE>Eleanor Banister</TITLE>
</HEADER><body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>Eleanor Banister</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/banister.jpg">

Eleanor Banister is a partner in King & Spalding's Labor, ERISA and Employment Law Group and has a comprehensive practice in employee benefits. She advises clients on the design, implementation and administration of employee benefit plans, executive compensation plans and the related funding vehicles.  Her practice also includes counseling with and negotiating on behalf of clients in connection with benefit issues that arise out of significant business transactions -- mergers, acquisitions, divestitures, and restructuring.
<P>
Ms. Banister has had significant experience representing institutional trustees in connection with their provision of trust and other services to sponsors of employee plans.  She also represents a major securities firm in connection with its retail prototype plan services, and represents lenders in the benefit aspects of loan transactions, including leveraged ESOPs.  Ms. Banister has served as a lecturer for the Southern Federal Tax Institute, the Georgia Society of Certified Public Accountants, the Southern Employee Benefits Conference, and the Institute of Continuing Legal Education in Georgia.  She serves on the Georgia Department of Human Resources, Division on Aging Services Pension Advisory Board and is Vice President/President Elect of the Southern Employee Benefits Conference.  Ms. Banister also is an active member of the Employee Benefits Committee of the Tax and Labor Sections of the American Bar Association.<P>

Ms. Banister graduated summa cum laude from the University of Georgia in 1973.  She also received her Juris Doctor degree, magna cum laude, from the University of Georgia in 1979.  Upon graduation she served as law clerk to The Honorable G. Ernest Tidwell, U.S. District Court Judge for the Northern District of Georgia.
<P>
