<HEADER>
<TITLE>Bernays T. Barclay</TITLE>
</HEADER><body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>Bernays T. Barclay</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/barclay.jpg">

Buz Barclay is a partner in the New York office of King & Spalding. His practice is concentrated in representing project investors and developers in connection with acquisitions, investments, development and regulations relating to energy-related project ventures, both domestic and international. He also represents energy-intensive industrial companies in dealings with utilities and other energy suppliers.  In addition, he is closely involved with the Firm's Project Finance Practice.
<P>
From 1979 to 1988, Mr. Barclay was extensively involved in the initial
defense and implementation of the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission
rules under the Public Utility Regulatory Policies Act of 1978 at the
Federal level and in over thirty states.
<P>
From 1988 to 1992, Mr. Barclay was a Vice President and Senior Banker
in the Project Finance Group of Citibank, N.A., where he was responsible
for originating, structuring, underwriting and syndicating large non
recourse project financings in the independent power and other industries.
<P>
He lectures on matters of project development, project finance
and regulatory law and has contributed articles to <EM>Infrastructure Finance,
Project Finance Monthly </EM>and other publications.
<P>
Mr. Barclay is a graduate of the University of Chicago Law School.
He holds an M.B.A. degree in Finance from Michigan State University,
and a bachelor's degree from the University of Michigan.
<P>
<P>
<A HREF="/menu/energy.htm">Energy & Independent Power Practice</A><P>
