<HEADER>
<TITLE>Patricia T. Barmeyer</TITLE>
</HEADER><body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>Patricia T. Barmeyer</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/barmeyer.jpg">

Patricia Barmeyer is a partner in King & Spalding's Environmental Practice Group. She joined the Firm in 1990, after serving 17 years as an assistant attorney general for the State of Georgia.
<P>
Ms. Barmeyer's practice involves environmental litigation in the state
and federal courts and administrative agencies.  Her work has focused
on permitting, compliance and litigation related to solid and hazardous
waste, Superfund and wetlands.  Ms. Barmeyer lectures
on topics relating to environmental issues.
<P>
On behalf of the State of Georgia, Ms. Barmeyer argued a natural resources
case in the United States Supreme Court and was involved in landmark
litigation involving beaches and coastal areas.  She also represented
the Georgia Environmental Protection Division in drafting and enforcing
laws and regulations related to solid and hazardous waste and other
environmental issues.
<P>
Ms. Barmeyer has been active in bar activities, having served as President
of the Atlanta Volunteer Lawyers Foundation and as a member of the Board
of Directors of the Atlanta Bar Association.  She is a member of the
American Bar Association, Section of Natural Resources, Energy and Environmental
Law, and a Fellow of the American Bar Foundation.
<P>
Ms. Barmeyer graduated from Hollins College in 1968 and from Harvard
University Law School, cum laude, in 1971.  She served two years as
law clerk to the Honorable Richard C. Freeman of the United States District
Court for the Northern District of Georgia.
<P>
