<HR>
<CENTER>
<H3><B>E. William Bates II</B></H3></CENTER><IMG
ALIGN="LEFT" VSPACE="10" HSPACE="10" SRC="/gif/bates.jpg">
<P>Bill Bates joined the Atlanta office of King &amp; Spalding in 1979,
initially focusing on financing transactions involving sales of securities.  Mr.
Bates currently heads up the Corporate Practice Group in the Firm's New York
office.</P>
<P>Mr. Bates has had significant experience in representing companies and
underwriters in public offerings and private placements of equity and debt
securities and in representing buyers and sellers in mergers and stock and cash
acquisition transactions, particularly within the insurance industry.  He also
has participated in a number of partnership structured finance transactions and
the establishment of managed investment funds.  </P>
<P>Mr. Bates graduated with highest honors from the University of North
Carolina in 1976.  He also received his law degree with the highest honors form
the University of North Carolina in 1979 and was a member of the Order of  the
Coif.  He was an editor of the <I>North Carolina Law Review</I>.</P>
