<HEADER>
<TITLE>Mary A. Bernard</TITLE>
</HEADER><body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>Mary A. Bernard</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/bernard.jpg">
<P>
Mary Bernard joined King & Spalding in 1988 and was elected partner in 1995.  She practices in the Firm's New York office. She has substantial experience in corporate finance transactions, including public offerings of equity and debt securities, as well as securities regulatory matters and merger and acquisition transactions.
<P>
Ms. Bernard has worked extensively in the representation of underwriters and corporate issuers in connection with public offerings of common stock (including low vote stocks), investment grade and high yield debt securities, "shelf" registrations and medium term note programs.  She also has broad experience in representing institutional investors in connection with private purchases of debt and equity securities.  In addition, Ms. Bernard advises public corporate clients regularly regarding corporate governance issues and SEC reporting and compliance issues, including disclosure obligations under Rule 10b-5, Section 16 and the proxy rules. 
<P>
Ms. Bernard graduated summa cum laude from the University of Minnesota in 1985 and received a Juris Doctorate Degree, magna cum laude, from the University of Minnesota in 1988.  She was a member of the Order of the Coif and served as an Articles Editor of the <EM>Minnesota Law Review</EM>.  Ms. Bernard is a member of the State Bar of Georgia and the American Bar Association.

<P>
<P>
<A HREF="/menu/corp.htm">Corporate Practice</A><P>
