<HEADER>
<TITLE>William Blumenthal</TITLE>
</HEADER><body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>William Blumenthal</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/blumenth.jpg">

William Blumenthal, a partner in the Washington, D.C. office of King
& Spalding, practices in the area of antitrust and trade regulation.
He has handled matters involving mergers, acquisitions, and joint ventures;
distribution restraints; alleged cartel behavior; advertising and marketing
practices; and contract and commercial disputes. Mr. Blumenthal appears regularly before the U.S. Department of Justice, the Federal Trade Commission, and the state Attorneys General.
<P>
Currently serving as a member of the governing Council of the ABA Antitrust
Section, Mr. Blumenthal previously chaired the Section's Clayton Act
Committee, which is responsible for activities relating to mergers
and joint ventures.  He is a member of the Board of Editors of the Matthew
Bender & Co. <EM>Antitrust Report</EM>.  His articles have appeared in <EM>Antitrust
Law Journal, Antitrust Bulletin, Regulation and the ABA's Developments
in Antitrust Health Care Law, </EM>among other publications.  He has spoken
at programs sponsored by the ABA, the Conference Board, the National
Health Lawyers Association, and other organizations.
<P>
Mr. Blumenthal holds an A.B. and M.A. from Brown University and a J.D.
from Harvard University.  After serving as a Teaching Fellow in the
Department of Economics at Harvard, he entered private practice in 1980.
He joined King & Spalding in 1995.
<P>
<P>
<A HREF="/menu/anti.htm">Antitrust Practice </A><P>
