<HEADER>
<TITLE>George S. Branch</TITLE>
</HEADER><body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>George S. Branch</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/branch.jpg">
<P>
George Branch joined King & Spalding in 1974 and was elected partner in 1980.  He received his law degree from the University of Virginia and his undergraduate degree from Yale University.  Mr. Branch has held a variety of administrative positions since his election to the partnership, including membership on the Firm's Policy and Compensation Committees and four years as a team leader of the Commercial Litigation Practice Group.
<P>
From 1974 to 1979, Mr. Branch practiced in the Firm's Commercial Department
where he focused on banking and commercial litigation.  He moved to
Washington, D. C. in 1979 to open the Firm's new Washington, D. C. office.
Upon returning to Atlanta in 1984, he concentrated exclusively in litigation
matters and currently represents clients on a broad range of general
commercial litigation and arbitration matters.
<P>
In addition to professional bar organizations, Mr. Branch serves on
the Board of Directors of Flagler, Inc. and the Board of Trustees of
Agnes Scott College.
<P>
<P>
<A HREF="/menu/comlit.htm">Commercial Litigation Practice</A><P>
