<HEADER>
<TITLE>Lanny B. Bridgers</TITLE>
</HEADER><body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>Lanny B. Bridgers</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/bridgers.jpg">
<P>
Lanny Bridgers is a partner in litigation, who has practiced in the Product Liability Practice Area of King & Spalding for more than twenty years.  His practice has been generally in the defense of domestic and foreign automobile manufacturers.  
<P>
He has tried cases on behalf of those clients in Georgia, Alabama, Kentucky and Mississippi and has been responsible for coordinating litigation in all of the southeastern states. 
<P>
Mr. Bridgers has addressed several seminars in the product liability area, including the Product Liability Seminar sponsored by the Defense Research Institute in December of 1988, the seminar on product liability sponsored by the Litigation Section of the American Bar Association in 1986, and the Product Liability Symposium sponsored by Southern Methodist University in 1982.  He was also a contributing author to the <EM>Masters Advocates' Handbook</EM> published by the National Institute for Trial Advocacy in 1986, and wrote the chapter on expert witnesses in Matthew Bender's <EM>Product Liability Practice Guide </EM>published in 1988.  
<P>
Mr. Bridgers is a member of the Litigation Section of the American Bar Association, a sustaining member of the Product Liability Advisory Council, and was Vice-Chairman of the Product Liability Committee of the Defense Research Institute. He is also a Fellow in the American College of Trial Lawyers and a Member of the American Board of Trial Advocates.
<P>
Mr. Bridgers graduated from the University of North Carolina in 1964.  Following four years in the Marine Corps, where he served as a Captain and Intelligence Officer, Mr. Bridgers received his law degree with high honors from the University of North Carolina in 1971 where he was a Special Editor of the <EM>North Carolina Law Review</EM> and a member of the National Moot Court Team.

<P>
<P>
<A HREF="/menu/prodliab.htm">Product Liability Practice</A><P>
