<CENTER><H3><B>Eileen P. Brumback</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/brumback.jpg">

Eileen Brumback is a Real Estate partner in King & Spalding's New York
office.  She joined the Firm in 1986 and was elected partner in 1993.
<P>
Ms. Brumback's practice encompasses a broad range of commercial real
estate law and includes the representation of domestic and foreign investors,
developers and lenders in the acquisition, development, financing and
sale of commercial properties.
<P>
After receiving her undergraduate degree from the University of North
Carolina in 1982, she earned her law degree from the University of Virginia
Law School in 1986.  She served as the Managing Editor of <EM>The Virginia
Journal of Natural Resources Law </EM>and is a member of the Association
of Real Estate Women and the American and Atlanta Bar Associations.
<P>
