<CENTER>
<H3><B>J. Kevin Buster</B></H3></CENTER><IMG
ALIGN="LEFT" VSPACE="10" HSPACE="10" SRC="/gif/buster.jpg">
<P>Kevin Buster is a litigation partner in King &amp; Spalding's Atlanta
office.  He chairs the Firm's Toxic Tort litigation department, which currently
consists of eleven attorneys devoted full-time to the defense of toxic tort
cases.  </P>
<P>Mr. Buster has substantial courtroom experience in a wide variety of cases,
including toxic tort, product liability, criminal, antitrust and commercial
cases.  Over the past decade, however, he has concentrated almost exclusively in
the defense of toxic tort cases.  He has defended toxic tort cases in the Firm's
home state of Georgia, as well as in the states of Alabama, Arkansas, Colorado,
Indiana, Kentucky, Louisiana, Mississippi, South Carolina, Tennessee and Texas. 
His cases have involved a variety of chemical substances, including the
following:</P>
<P>- dioxin <BR>- PCBs</P>
<P>- pesticides<BR>- toxaphene</P>
<UL>
<LI> 2,4-D
</LI>
<LI> 2,4,5-T
</LI>
<LI> chlorpyrifos (Dursban)
</LI>
<LI> chlordane
</LI>
<LI> others
</LI></UL>
<P>- mercury<BR>- petroleum products<BR>- methane and hydrogen sulfide<BR>-
solvents</P>
<UL>
<LI> TCE</LI>
<LI> methylene chloride
</LI>
<LI> others
</LI></UL>
<P>Mr. Buster received his undergraduate degree from Duke University (summa cum
laude, Phi Beta Kappa), and his law degree from the University of Virginia (top
5%).  He joined King &amp; Spalding after a clerkship with the Honorable Pierce
Lively of the United States Court of Appeals for the Sixth Circuit.</P>
<P><A HREF="/menu/toxic.htm">Toxic Tort Practice</A></P>
