<TITLE>John D. Capers, Jr.</TITLE>
</HEADER><body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>John D. Capers, Jr.</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/capers.jpg">

Jack Capers is a partner in King & Spalding's Corporate Finance and International Practice Group. He joined the Firm in 1978 and was elected partner in 1985.
<P>
Mr. Capers has experience in a wide variety of corporate transactions, including domestic and international mergers, acquisitions, securities offerings, joint ventures and governmental and quasi-governmental borrowings. He represents non-U.S. clients in their U.S. business activities, including public and private company clients from the U.K., Germany and the Middle East. Mr. Capers' most recent international transactions include joint ventures involving projects in the U.K., France and Germany.
<P>
Mr. Capers is actively involved in a number of civic activities in Atlanta, including Egleston Children's Hospital at Emory University and the Metropolitan Atlanta Crime Commission.
<P>
Mr. Capers graduated from Vanderbilt University with high honors in 1975. He received his law degree from the University of Georgia School of Law in 1978, where he served as Articles Editor of the <EM>Georgia Law Review </EM>in 1977-78. He graduated from Georgia with highest honors and was a member of the Order of Coif.<P>
<P>
