<TITLE>Fred G. Codner</TITLE>
</HEADER><body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>Fred G. Codner</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/codner.jpg">

Fred Codner is a member of the Litigation Practice Group focusing on complex construction and commercial litigation matters. He joined King & Spalding in 1987 and became counsel in 1995. 
<P>
He has focused his practice on representing litigants in cases involving complex commercial transactions. He has extensive experience representing banks and secured lenders in the area of lender liability and the investigation of fraud. Mr. Codner has also acquired significant experience in the area of insolvent debtors and bankruptcy litigation. 
<P>
Mr. Codner is a certified arbitrator and mediator on behalf of the American Arbitration Association. He also routinely acts as an arbitrator on behalf of the Superior Court of Fulton County, Georgia. 
<P>
A 1983 graduate of the University of Georgia with a B.A. degree, magna cum laude, Mr. Codner attended the University of Michigan Law School, where he was an Associate Editor of the <EM>Michigan Law Review. </EM>He graduated the University of Michigan Law School in 1986 cum laude. Following law school, he worked as a law clerk to the Honorable Elbert P. Tuttle of the United States Court of Appeals for the Eleventh Circuit. 
<P>
<P>
<A HREF="/menu/condev.htm">Construction & Development Practice</A><P>
