<HEADER>
<TITLE>Timothy F. Coen</TITLE>
</HEADER><body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>Timothy F. Coen</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/coen.jpg">
<P>
<P>
Timothy F. Coen is counsel to King & Spalding's Intellectual Property and Technology practice group in the Atlanta office. He joined the Firm in 1996 concentrating in the telecommunications and high technology areas.
<p>
Prior to joining the Firm, Mr. Coen most recently served as Associate General Counsel of Concert Communications Company, a global telecommunications joint venture company. Previously, Mr. Coen also served as Mergers and Acquisitions Counsel to BellSouth Enterprises, Inc. and Regulatory General Attorney for BellSouth Telecommunications, Inc. 
<P>
Mr. Coen has extensive experience in transactional and regulatory matters pertaining to the local exchange business and other domestic and international telecommunications markets. Mr. Coen is experienced in the structuring and negotiation of sophisticated telecommunications outsourcing, networking, interconnection and other service agreements; in the handling of domestic and international telecom acquisitions and joint ventures; in technology licensing and procurement matters and other high technology transactions.
<P>
Mr. Coen, an honors graduate of the University of Georgia School of Law and Notes Editor of the <EM>Georgia Law Review, </EM>is admitted to practice in the state of Georgia and the District of Columbia. He is a member of the Federal Communications Bar Association, the International Bar Association and the American Bar Association. Previously, Mr. Coen was the featured speaker at the ABA Annual Meeting, Inter-American Law Committee, International Law Section, regarding "Recent Developments - Service Agreements in Latin America."
<P>
<A HREF="/menu/ipt.htm">Intellectual Property & Technology Practice</A><P>
