<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>David L. Coker</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/coker.jpg">

David Coker is a partner in King & Spalding's Real Estate Practice and
serves as a Team Leader.  He has been involved in a broad range of commercial
and real estate transactions on behalf of developers and foreign and
domestic investors.
<P>
Mr. Coker has had substantial involvement in representing both developers
and department stores in regional malls, the most recent of which is
a mall located in metropolitan Charlotte, North Carolina.
<P>
He has served as Chairman of the Real Property Division of the State
Bar of Georgia and is a member of the American College of Real Estate
Lawyers.  He has served on numerous civic and charitable boards, including
the Woodruff Arts Center, the Alliance Theatre (former Chairman), and
the Stone Mountain Memorial Association, the State authority which owns
and operates Stone Mountain Park.
<P>
Mr. Coker received both his undergraduate and law degrees from Emory
University, where he was a member of Omicron Delta Kappa and Editor
in-Chief of the <EM>Journal of Public Law.</EM>
