<TITLE>Dwight J. Davis</TITLE>
</HEADER><body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>Dwight J. Davis</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/davisd.jpg">

Dwight Davis is a partner in the Litigation Practice at King & Spalding. He joined the Firm in 1982 and was elected partner in 1989.
<P>
Throughout his practice, Mr. Davis has had litigation and trial experience in a wide range of civil matters including securities fraud, antitrust, consumer fraud, and complex class action litigation.  In recent years, most of his work has involved dealer, franchise and distribution disputes.
<P>
He has served as lead counsel or co-lead counsel in a number of major cases in both state and federal courts for large multi-national companies. He has worked on several internal investigations for large financial and oil companies and represents the Atlanta Committee for the Olympic Games on issues related to risk management and insurance.
<P>
Mr. Davis has lectured at seminars on business torts, RICO, and discovery
issues for the Georgia Institute of Continuing Legal Education, and
serves on the faculty of the Emory University School of Law trial practice
program.
<P>
Mr. Davis is active in a number of civic activities and currently
serves on the Board of Directors of Goodwill Industries of Atlanta and
on the Board of Visitors of Mercer University School of Law.
<P>
Mr. Davis graduated magna cum laude from The Citadel in 1975.  He served
in the United States Army Infantry for four years.  He graduated magna
cum laude from the Mercer University School of Law in 1982, where he
was the editor of the <EM>Mercer Law Review, </EM>Eleventh Circuit Survey.
<P>
<P>
