<HEADER>
<TITLE>Frederick H. Degnan</TITLE>
</HEADER><body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>Frederick H. Degnan</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/degnan.jpg">

Fred Degnan, a partner in the Washington, D.C. office, joined King
& Spalding in 1988,  bringing over 11 years of broad FDA experience.
He heads the Food Group at King & Spalding where he handles a range
of food safety and labeling issues.
<P>
From 1980 to 1988, Mr. Degnan served as FDA's Associate Chief Counsel
for Foods.  His career at FDA included extensive experience with food
issues including safety, nutrition and health, labeling, good manufacturing
practice, packaging and the use of risk assessment and risk management
in the regulation of carcinogenic components of food.
<P>
He has substantial litigation and enforcement responsibilities and
appeared on behalf of FDA in over 30 states.  He also conducted several
administrative hearings, most notably cyclamate and the agency's only
"imminent hazard" hearing, phenformin.
<P>
In conjunction with his food law work, for five years Mr.
Degnan handled all legal issues at FDA concerning drug abuse.  He served
as Chairman of the Interagency Council on Drug Control and was one of
the primary drafters of legislation to combat "designer drugs."
<P>
Mr. Degnan twice received the FDA Award of Merit, the agency's highest
award.  He has published and taught on a wide array of food and drug
issues.  Since 1989, in addition to his responsibilities at the Firm,
he has served as an adjunct professor of law at the Columbus School
of Law, Catholic University of America, teaching food and drug law.
<P>
He is a graduate of Holy Cross College and received his law degree
from Georgetown University in 1973.
<P>
<P>
<A HREF="/menu/food.htm">Food & Drug Practice</A><P>
