<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>Thomas K. Dotzenrod</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/dotzenrd.jpg">

Tom Dotzenrod joined King & Spalding in 1985, was elected partner in
1993, and practices in the Commercial Real Estate Group.  He has
represented both developer and lender clients in a wide variety of real
estate transactions, with an emphasis on lender representation in loan
transactions and restructurings.
<P>
Mr. Dotzenrod received his undergraduate degree from Brown University
in 1982 and received his law degree, with distinction, from Emory University
School of Law in 1985.  He is a member of Order of the Coif and was
a Notes and Comments editor of the <EM>Emory Law Journal.</EM>
<P>
