<HEADER>
<TITLE>Bernadette Drankoski</TITLE>
</HEADER><body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>Bernadette Drankoski</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/drankosk.jpg">
<P>
Bernadette Drankoski is a partner in King & Spalding's Corporate Practice Group, working on domestic and international corporate matters. She joined the Firm in 1986 and practices in the Atlanta office.
<P>
Ms. Drankoski has represented U.S. and non-U.S. clients in acquisitions, mergers, investment partnerships, joint ventures, restructurings of under-performing investments and a wide variety of contract matters.
<P>
In addition, Ms. Drankoski works extensively with sponsors of domestic and cross-border investment funds.  She has worked with sponsors to form funds that invest in venture capital, real estate, leveraged buy-outs and distressed companies.  She also counsels investment fund advisors and investors. 
<P>
After receiving her undergraduate degree with high honors from Harvard College in 1980, Ms. Drankoski earned her law degree from the University of Virginia in 1985. She was an Executive Editor of the <EM>Virginia Tax Review, </EM>and a member of the Order of the Coif. Upon graduation, she served as a law clerk to the Honorable Thomas A. Clark of the United States Eleventh Circuit Court of Appeals.<P>
<A HREF="/menu/corp.htm">Corporate Practice</A><P>
