<HEADER>
<TITLE>William S. Duffey, Jr.</TITLE>
</HEADER><body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>William S. Duffey, Jr.</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/duffey.jpg">

Bill Duffey was elected a partner at King & Spalding in 1987.  From
1994 to 1995, he served on the staff of the Office of Independent Counsel
investigating President and Mrs. Clinton's involvement in Whitewater.
He served as Deputy Independent Counsel in charge of the Arkansas phase
of the investigation.  He rejoined the Firm as a partner following government
service.
<P>
Mr. Duffey's practice includes complex criminal and civil litigation
and internal corporate investigations.  He has lectured and written for continuing legal
education programs on white collar crime,  civil litigation techniques,
settlement negotiations, and alternative dispute resolution systems
and procedures.
<P>
He is a member of the Board of Trustees of Drake University and served
as Chairman of the Atlanta Bar Association Committee on Alternate Dispute
Resolution and as a member of the Fulton County Bench-Bar Committee
on Alternate Dispute Resolution.
<P>
An honors graduate of Drake University in 1973, Mr. Duffey received
his J.D., cum laude, in 1977 from  the University of South Carolina
Law School,  where he served as Articles Editor of the <EM>South Carolina
Law Review. </EM>Mr. Duffey served in the United States Air Force Judge Advocate
General Corps from 1978-1981. During that time, he held the position
of Circuit Trial Counsel, prosecuting more than 30 felony cases in eight
southeastern states and the Republic of Panama.  Mr. Duffey was an Assistant
Staff Judge Advocate to the United States Logistics Group in Ankara,
Turkey, where he served as legal advisor to the United States forces
in Saudi Arabia.
<P>
<P>
<A HREF="/menu/special.htm">Special Matters Practice</A><P>
