<TITLE>William L. Durham II</TITLE>
</HEADER><body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>William L. Durham II</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/durham.jpg">

Bill Durham joined King & Spalding's Litigation Practice in 1990.  He was elected counsel in 1995 and practices in the Atlanta office. Mr. Durham's litigation experience includes a broad range of commercial civil disputes in state and federal courts. He also has represented clients before such governmental agencies as the Securities and Exchange Commission.
<P>
In 1982, Mr. Durham graduated with highest honors from the University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill, where he was  a member of Phi Beta Kappa.  In 1985, he earned his J.D. from the University of Virginia, where he was Executive Editor of the <EM>Virginia Law Review </EM>and was elected to membership in the Order of the Coif.  He served as a law clerk to the Hon. Clement F. Haynsworth, Jr., Senior Judge of the U.S. Court of Appeals for the Fourth Circuit.  He is a member of the State Bars of California and Georgia, as well as The District of Columbia Bar and the American Bar Association.
<P>
<P>
