<HEAD>
<TITLE>Michael J. Egan III</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#00009c" VLINK="#8e2323">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER></CENTER>
<HR>
<CENTER>
<H3><B>Michael J. Egan III</B></H3></CENTER><IMG
ALIGN="LEFT" VSPACE="10" HSPACE="10" SRC="/gif/egan.jpg">
<P>Mike Egan is a partner in King &amp; Spalding's Atlanta office. He joined
King &amp; Spalding in 1983 and heads the Firm's Corporate Practice Group.</P>
<P>His primary practice areas include mergers and acquisitions, joint ventures
and corporate finance transactions. Mr. Egan has substantial experience
representing investment funds and corporations in leveraged transactions and in
representing U.S. companies in international transactions.</P>
<P>From 1989-91, Mr. Egan lived in Duesseldorf, Germany and London, England on
temporary assignment for The Coca-Cola Company. During this period Mr. Egan
served as European Finance Counsel to The Coca-Cola Company, acting on its
behalf in transactions in Germany, Belgium, The Netherlands, Italy, Portugal and
Greece. Mr. Egan also spent part of this period with Bruckhaus Westrick &amp;
Stegemann in Duesseldorf, a major German law firm.</P>
<P>Mr. Egan received his J.D., cum laude, from Harvard Law School in 1982, and
was a Phi Beta Kappa graduate and Morehead Scholar at the University of North
Carolina-Chapel Hill. Mr. Egan is currently Co-President of the Alumni
Association of The Westminster Schools in Atlanta. </P>
<P><A HREF="/menu/corp.htm">Corporate Practice</A></P>
