<HEADER>
<TITLE>Steven J. Estep</TITLE>
</HEADER><body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>Steven J. Estep</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/estep.jpg">
<P>
Steve Estep has been involved in the Litigation Practice since joining
King & Spalding in 1988.  He was elected partner in 1995.
<P>
Mr. Estep focuses his practice on the defense of products liability
cases, with a particular emphasis on matters involving automobile design.
He also has an active practice in property tax litigation, representing
property owners in cases against state, county and local taxing authorities.
<P>
His experience includes trials and appeals in the federal and state
courts in Georgia, and he represents clients in cases throughout the
Southeast.
<P>
Mr. Estep is a member of the American Bar Association, serving particularly
on its Litigation Section's Product Liability Committee and Legislation
Subcommittee.
<P>
A 1985 graduate of Florida State University, Mr. Estep received his
law degree summa cum laude from Mercer University in 1988.  He received
eleven American Jurisprudence Awards while at Mercer, where he was a
member of the <EM>Mercer Law Review </EM>staff.  He also was awarded the Woodruff
Medal, the school's highest individual academic honor.
<P>
<P>
<A HREF="/menu/prodliab.htm">Product Liability Practice</A><P>
<p><center>
<HR>
