<HEADER>
<TITLE>Suzanne C. Feese</TITLE>
</HEADER><body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>Suzanne C. Feese</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/feese.jpg">

Suzanne Feese practices in King & Spalding's Tax Practice in the Atlanta office. She joined King & Spalding in 1988 and was elected partner in 1994.
<P>
Her practice focuses on a range of business tax issues, with particular
emphasis on the taxation of partnerships and the taxation of foreign
persons with U.S. activities.  She also has significant experience representing
clients in complex partnership and structured financing transactions.
<P>
Ms. Feese earned her law degree from Yale University in 1987, where
she worked as an Assistant-in-Instruction in the law school from 1986-1987.  She received her bachelor's degree with honors from Agnes Scott
College.  From 1987-1988, Ms. Feese was Law Clerk to the Hon. R. Lanier
Anderson III of the U.S. Court of Appeals for the Eleventh Circuit.
She is a member of the State Bar of Georgia and the American Bar Association.
<P>
<P>
<A HREF="/menu/tax.htm">Tax Practice</A><P>
