<HEADER>
<TITLE>Paul K. Ferdinands</TITLE>
</HEADER><body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>Paul K. Ferdinands</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/ferdnds.jpg">

Paul Ferdinands joined King & Spalding in 1986 and was elected partner in the Firm's Bankruptcy and Commercial Litigation Practice in 1994.  His practice encompasses a broad range of bankruptcy matters and includes the representation of debtors, secured and unsecured creditors, lenders in connection with debtor in possession and plan of reorganization financings, and purchasers of assets of bankrupt entities.
<P>
Mr. Ferdinands received his law degree from Stanford University in
1986 and his bachelor's degree, with high distinction in economics,
from the University of Virginia in 1983.  He is a member of the State
Bar of Georgia and the Atlanta and American Bar Associations.
<P>
<P>
<A HREF="/menu/bankrupt.htm">Bankruptcy & Commercial Litigation Practice</A><P>
