<TITLE>William B. Fryer</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#00009c" VLINK="#8e2323">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER></CENTER>
<HR>
<CENTER>
<H3><B>William B. Fryer</B></H3></CENTER><IMG
ALIGN="LEFT" VSPACE="10" HSPACE="10" SRC="/gif/fryer.jpg">
<P>Bill Fryer is a partner in the Atlanta office of King &amp; Spalding.  He
joined the Firm in 1974 and was elected a partner in 1980.  </P>
<P>Mr. Fryer is a corporate lawyer whose practice includes mergers,
acquisitions, financings and project developments, with an emphasis on real
estate securitizations.  </P>
<P>Mr. Fryer received both his undergraduate and law degrees from the
University of Virginia (B.A., with high honors and with high distinction in
1971; J.D. in 1974).  He is a member Phi Beta Kappa, Omicron and Delta Kappa. 
Mr. Fryer served on the Editorial Board of the <I>Virginia Law Review</I> and
is a member of the Order of the Coif.  </P>
<P>From 1990 until 1992, Mr. Fryer served as a member of the Firm's Policy
Committee.  He is a member of the Atlanta and American Bar Associations, the
State Bar of Georgia, and a Trustee of The Lovett School.</P>
<P></P>
<P><A HREF="/menu/real.htm">Real Estate Practice</A></P>
