<TITLE>Thomas B. Gaines, Jr.</TITLE>
</HEADER><body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>Thomas B. Gaines, Jr.</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/gaines.jpg">

Thomas Gaines is a member of the Intellectual Property and Technology
Practice Group in the Atlanta office.  His practice focuses on a full
range of corporate transactions involving the acquisition, exploitation
and protection of intellectual property and technology assets.
<P>
He joined the Firm in 1987 and became counsel in 1994.  He is admitted
to practice in Florida and in Georgia and is a member of The Florida
Bar, the State Bar of Georgia, the Atlanta Bar Association and the American
Bar Association.
<P>
Mr. Gaines received his J.D., with high honors, in 1986 from Florida
State University, where he also received a B.S. in Political Science
in 1982.  While at Florida State law school, he was a member of the
<EM>Florida State University Law Review </EM>(1985-1986), and in 1986-1987 served
as a clerk for the Honorable Paul H. Roney, Chief Judge, U.S. Court
of Appeals for the Eleventh Circuit.
<P>
<P>
<A HREF="/menu/ipt.htm">Intellectual Property & Technology Practice</A><P>
