<HEADER>
<TITLE>Peter J. Genz</TITLE>
</HEADER><body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>Peter J. Genz</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/genz.jpg">

Peter Genz is a tax partner in the Atlanta office of King & Spalding.
He joined the Firm in 1982 and was elected a partner in 1988.
<P>
His practice concentrates in corporate, partnership, and real estate
tax matters and tax controversies.  Mr. Genz is particularly qualified
in matters relating to structuring inbound foreign investment, real
estate investment trusts and troubled company workouts.
<P>
Mr. Genz served as an attorney-advisor to Chief Judge Howard A.
Dawson, Jr. of the United States Tax Court from 1980-82.  He has published
a number of articles on tax subjects and is a frequent speaker on corporate,
partnership and international tax matters.
<P>
A graduate of the University of Florida (B.S.B.A., magna cum laude,
1975), Mr. Genz earned his law degree from the University of Florida
Law School (cum laude, 1980).  He received a master's degree in taxation
from the Georgetown University Law Center in 1982.
<P>
<P>
<A HREF="/menu/tax.htm">Tax Practice</A><P>
