<TITLE>W. Clay Gibson</TITLE>
</HEADER><body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>W. Clay Gibson</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/gibson.jpg">

Clay Gibson joined King & Spalding in 1981 and was elected partner
in 1988.  He is a member of the Firm's Commercial Real Estate Group
and has represented clients in connection with the acquisition and development
of, and investment in, shopping centers, office buildings, and other
commercial property.  He also represents both landlords and tenants
in connection with retail and office leases.
<P>
Mr. Gibson has been active in the American Cancer Society and currently
is Chairman of the Board of the Atlanta City Unit and serves on the
Board of the Georgia Division.
<P>
A graduate with distinction of the University of Virginia in 1978,
he received  his J.D. with distinction from Emory University School
of Law in 1981, where was a member of the Order of the Coif and the
Board of Editors of the <EM>Emory Law Journal.</EM>
<P>
<P>
<A HREF="/menu/real.htm">Real Estate Practice</A><P>
