<HEADER>
<TITLE>James N. Gorsline</TITLE>
</HEADER><body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>James N. Gorsline</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/gorsline.jpg">

Jim Gorsline is a member of King & Spalding's Bankruptcy and Commercial
Litigation Group.  He joined the Firm in 1985 as an associate and was
named counsel in 1993.
<P>
Mr. Gorsline has focused his practice on representing litigants in
cases involving complicated accounting transactions or complex damage
calculations.  He has particular experience representing accountants
in accounting malpractice and securities fraud cases.
<P>
A Certified Public Accountant, Mr. Gorsline worked for a "Big-Eight" accounting
firm prior to attending law school.  In 1985, he graduated magna cum
laude from the University of South Carolina, where he was a member of
the <EM>Law Review </EM>and elected to the Order of the Coif.
<P>
<P>
<A HREF="/menu/bankrupt.htm">Bankruptcy & Commercial Litigation Practice</A><P>
