<TITLE>S. Samuel Griffin</TITLE>
</HEADER><body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>S. Samuel Griffin</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/griffins.jpg">
<P>
Sam Griffin practices in King & Spalding's Product Liability Practice Group. He joined the Firm in 1986 and was elected partner in 1994.
<P>
Mr. Griffin has a broad commercial litigation practice, with a particular
emphasis on products liability matters. In addition, he also has represented
manufacturers in connection with dealership terminations and other disputes.
<P>
He currently is a member of the American Bar Association Litigation
Section, the ABA's Committee on Products Liability Litigation and the
Georgia Products Liability Committee.
<P>
Mr. Griffin graduated cum laude from Vanderbilt University in 1983.
He received his J.D. in 1986 from Vanderbilt University School of Law,
where he served on the Vanderbilt Law Review and was a member of the
Order of the Coif.
<P>
