<HEADER>
<TITLE>Sandra W. Hallmark</TITLE>
</HEADER><body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>Sandra W. Hallmark</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/hallmark.jpg">

Sandi Hallmark joined King & Spalding in the Washington, D.C., office
in 1987 and became a partner in 1993.  Ms. Hallmark's practice covers
a broad range of business tax issues, with particular emphasis on the
taxation of partnerships.  She also has significant experience representing
clients in complex partnership and structured financing transactions.
<P>
Ms. Hallmark is a co-author of the treatise <EM>Federal Taxation of Partnerships
and Partners: Structuring and Drafting Agreements.</EM>
<P>
Prior to joining the Firm, Ms. Hallmark served as Attorney-Advisor
in the Legislation & Regulations Division of the Internal Revenue Service
Office of Chief Counsel.  In that position she assisted in the development
of tax regulations, rulings and other tax policy matters.
<P>
Ms. Hallmark received her undergraduate degree from Brandeis University
in 1977.  She received her law degree from the Benjamin N. Cardozo School
of Law in 1983 and a Masters of Laws in Taxation from Georgetown University
in 1986.
<P>
