<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>Michael J. Hannigan</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/hannigan.jpg">
<P>
Mike Hannigan has over 20 years of experience serving as counsel in connection with  various types of financial transactions. Formerly a partner at Mudge Rose in New York, he  joined King & Spalding as a partner in November 1995. 
<P>
Mr. Hannigan concentrates on public finance matters, representing primarily commercial banks, investment banking firms and other financial institutions in both the primary and secondary markets. He has considerable experience in resource recovery, public power and other energy-related financings. He frequently serves as counsel to banks and other credit enhancers of tax-exempt debt and has worked extensively on municipal transactions involving interest rate swaps.
<P>
Mr. Hannigan was born in Corinth, New York. He graduated from Dartmouth College in 1971 (A.B., cum laude). He received his J.D. from Georgetown University in 1974 where he was a member of the<EM> Georgetown Law Journal</EM>. He is a member of the New York Bar Association.
<P>
