<CENTER><H3><B>Jon R. Harris, Jr.</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/harris.jpg">

Jon Harris joined King & Spalding in 1984 as a member of the Corporate Practice focusing in the Healthcare Practice area. He was elected a partner in 1991.
<P>
His practice includes general corporate work, public and private offerings
of equity and debt securities, venture capital financings, leveraged
buyout transactions and regulatory advice with respect to insurance
and investment adviser matters, with significant experience in mergers
and acquisitions of healthcare, industrial service, manufacturing and
distribution companies.
<P>
Mr. Harris received a Bachelor of Arts degree (magna cum laude) from
Vanderbilt University in 1980.  He received a Doctor of Jurisprudence
and a Masters of Business Administration (with highest honors) from
Vanderbilt University in 1984.  Mr. Harris served as the Editor-in-Chief
of the <EM>Vanderbilt Journal of Transnational Law.</EM>
