<HEADER>
<TITLE>Joseph B. Haynes</TITLE>
</HEADER><body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>Joseph B. Haynes</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/haynes.jpg">

Barney Haynes is a partner concentrating in civil litigation.  He joined King & Spalding in 1969 and was elected a partner in 1975.
<P>
Mr. Haynes has extensive experience in commercial litigation, and he has represented numerous clients of the Firm in complex cases in state and federal courts and arbitrations, both in Georgia and in other parts of the country.  He has broad litigation and trial experience in a variety of civil matters, including professional liability, antitrust, commercial contract litigation, franchisor-franchisee relationships, securities, internal corporate investigations, class action lawsuits, derivative shareholder suits, civil RICO claims, banking litigation and construction contract suits.
<P>
Mr. Haynes was elected to the American College of Trial Lawyers in 1992.  He is a member of the litigation and antitrust sections of the American Bar, and the State Bar of Georgia.  He is also a member of  the State Bar of New York.
<P>
Mr. Haynes graduated cum laude from the University of the South in 1962, where he was Phi Beta Kappa and was the recipient of the Algernon Sidney Sullivan Award.  He was a Root Tilden Scholar at New York University School of Law, where he graduated in 1965 and was awarded the Benjamin F. Butler Prize for Excellence.  He was a Judge Advocate General and a Captain in the United States Air Force from 1966 through 1969, where he concentrated on court-martials as a trial judge advocate.
<P>
He is a trustee of the Jesse Parker Williams Foundation.  He has served as an elder of the Peachtree Presbyterian Church, chairman of the Board of Deacons of the Peachtree Presbyterian Church, trustee of the Atlanta Cancer Society, member of the Public Affairs Committee of Atlanta Chamber of Commerce, a trustee of Christ School, and a past president of the Sewanee Club of Atlanta.<P>
<P><P>
