<HEADER>
<TITLE>Robert D. Hays, Jr.</TITLE>
</HEADER><body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>Robert D. Hays, Jr.</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/hays.jpg">
<P>
Robert Hays joined King & Spalding in 1983 and was elected partner
in 1990.  He currently serves as Team Leader of the Product Liability
Practice.
<P>
Mr. Hays has had experience in a variety of litigation matters and
has been lead counsel in jury trials in both state and federal courts.
Mr. Hays concentrates in product liability and toxic tort matters.
<P>
In addition, Mr. Hays has been involved in litigation concerning libel
and slander, insurance issues, zoning and land-use disputes, RICO, employment
law and other commercial matters.
<P>
Mr. Hays is Vice-Chairman of the American Bar Association's TIPS Product
Liability Section, and a member of the American Bar Association Litigation
Section and Product Liability Section.  He is also a member of the Defense
Research Institute, the Georgia Defense Lawyers Association, and founding
member of the Georgia Product Liability Committee.  He has participated
in various seminars and publications on product liability matters.
<P>
In 1983, he received his law degree from Vanderbilt University, where
he was a member of the <EM>Vanderbilt Law Review.</EM>  He graduated summa cum
laude and was Phi Beta Kappa at the University of North Carolina at
Chapel Hill in 1980.
<P>
<P>
