<CENTER><H3><B>Theodore M. Hester</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/hester.jpg">

Ted Hester joined King & Spalding in 1977 and is the head of the Governmental
Practice Group in the Washington, D.C. office.  He served as Partner
in-Charge of the Washington office from 1983 through 1992, and as a
member of the Firm's Policy Committee from 1986 to 1991.  Mr. Hester
represents clients on congressional investigative and legislative matters,
and before various executive departments.
<P>
Mr. Hester is a member of the Board of Directors of the Ethics Resource
Center. He is the Out of State Member of the Board of Governors of the
State Bar of Georgia and is a member of the Board of the Children's
National Medical Center.  He is a past president of the National Association
of Bond Lawyers and of the Younger Lawyers Section of the State Bar
of Georgia.  He served as a member of the Anthony Commission on Public
Finance.
<P>
Mr. Hester is a graduate of Harvard University Law School (J.D., 1969)
and the University of Georgia (A.B., 1966).  He lectures and writes, notably on matters related to government, policy and politics.
