<CENTER><H3><B>G. Lemuel Hewes</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/hewes.jpg">

Lem Hewes is a partner in King & Spalding's Banking and Finance Practice Group.  He has a broad range of experience in commercial and banking law, including secured and unsecured loan transactions, workouts, bankruptcy, bank-related litigation and bank regulatory matters. He also recently became involved in several international financing matters, two involving privatizations in the Czech Republic.
<P>
Mr. Hewes has practiced law at King & Spalding for 30 years.  He is an associate member of the Conference of State Bank Supervisors, an organization of state bank regulators, as well as an Advisory Board Member of the Southern Banking Law Conference.  He is on the Board of Directors for the Childhood Autism Diagnostic and Educational Foundation <EM>(CADEF), </EM>and serves on the advisory board for Emory University's Autism Resource Center.  He is also on the advisory board of the National Center for Paralegal Training.
<P>
A 1962 graduate of Vanderbilt University, he earned his J.D. from Harvard University in 1965, where he received his Phi Beta Kappa award.  He is a member of the Atlanta Bar Association, the State Bar of Georgia and the American Bar Association, including serving as a member of the Developments in Business Financing Committee.
