<TITLE>William A. Holby</TITLE>
</HEADER><body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>William A. Holby</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/holby.jpg">

Bill Holby joined King & Spalding in 1979, and was elected partner in 1986.  He practices in Atlanta with the Public Finance Group.<P>
He concentrates on public finance transactions, with a focus on the representation of domestic and foreign financial institutions that provide credit and liquidity facilities to support municipal obligations.  <P>
Mr. Holby regularly serves as bond counsel and as counsel to credit enhancers in connection with financings for city and county governments; hospitals, universities, and other tax-exempt organizations; utilities; and other beneficiaries of public securities.<P>
A frequent faculty member at seminars conducted by the National Association of Bond Lawyers, Mr. Holby regularly speaks on topics relating to credit enhancement, structured finance transactions, and the bond rating process.  He is a member of the Steering Committee for the Bond Attorneys Workshop conducted annually in Chicago, Illinois.<P>
A cum laude graduate of Vanderbilt University in 1976, Mr. Holby received his law degree from Vanderbilt University in 1979.<P>
<P>
