<HTML>
<HEADER>
<TITLE>Michael R. Horten</TITLE>
</HEADER><body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>Michael R. Horten</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/horten.jpg">
<P>
Michael Horten is a partner in King & Spalding's International Practice
Group.  His practice involves the representation of U.S. companies with
respect to their investments and business activities overseas and the
representation of foreign companies with respect to their investments
and business activities in the United States.
<P>
Mr. Horten has experience in a wide variety of international corporate,
commercial and financial transactions, including structuring, negotiating
and effecting international joint ventures and strategic alliances,
cross border acquisitions, cross border technology transfers and licensing
arrangements, and cross border financial arrangements, such as double
dip lease transactions.
<P>
His writings include articles in <EM>Tax Management International Journal,
Tax Planning International Review, Investment/USA</EM> and <EM>Kokusai Shoji
Homu </EM>(The Journal of the Japanese Institute of International Business
Law).  Mr. Horten is the author of the booklet <EM>U.S. Joint Ventures </EM>(Ohrlings,
Stockholm).  Mr. Horten is also the co-author with Philippe Sarrailhe
of the book <EM>Les Joint-Ventures Franco-Americaines </EM>(1994, Larcier, Brussels;
and Forum Europeen de la Communication, Paris) and is the co-author
with Karl-Erbo Kageneck of the book <EM>Joint Ventures in den USA: Wirtschaftliche,
Rechtliche und Steuerliche Aspekte </EM>(1995, C.H. Beck'sche Verlagsbuchhandlung,
Munich).  He has lectured before professional seminars in the United
States, Europe and Asia.
<P>
A member of the Board of Directors of the Japan-America Society of
Georgia, Georgia Council of International Visitors and the Swedish American
Chamber of Commerce, Mr. Horten is also active in a number of international
organizations, including the International Bar Association, the Atlanta
Chamber of Commerce, Society of International Business Fellows, World
Trade Club of Atlanta and several Atlanta based bilateral chambers of
commerce.
<P>
Born in Copenhagen, Denmark, and now living in Atlanta, Georgia, Mr.
Horten did his undergraduate study at Washington State University.
His legal education includes law degrees from the University of Copenhagen
and Columbia University, and course work for a doctorate in EEC law
at the University of Paris.  Until 1973, Mr. Horten practiced law in
New York and Paris.  Mr. Horten has been with King & Spalding since
1973.  Mr. Horten speaks French, German, Danish, Swedish and Norwegian.
<P>
<P>
<A HREF="/menu/corp.htm">Corporate Practice</A><P>
