<TITLE>R. Anthony Howard, Jr.</TITLE>
</HEADER><body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>R. Anthony Howard, Jr.</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/howard.jpg">

Tony Howard joined King & Spalding in 1985 and was elected partner in 1993. Prior to attending the Univerisity of Notre Dame Law School, he was a Research Assistant in the Department of Pharmacology of Georgetown University Medical School, a position that provides valuable background experience for Mr. Howard's role in the Firm's Pharmaceutical and Medical Device Practices.  
<P>
Since joining King & Spalding, Mr. Howard has had extensive experience
in all aspects of the Firm's Food and Drug Practice, including administrative
and civil litigation involving pharmaceutical regulatory issues, Freedom
of Information Act disclosure, and regulatory fraud.  He has also been
active in counseling clients in the brand name and generic pharmaceutical, biotechnology, and medical device industries on FDA regulatory enforcement and compliance matters.
<P>
Mr. Howard is active in the Food and Drug Law Institute and the Regulatory
Affairs Professionals Society, organizations for which he has lectured on pharmaceutical and medical device issues.  At Notre Dame,
Mr. Howard served as Executive Editor of the <EM>Journal of Legislation
</EM>and he was the 1984-85 James P. Lardy Scholar.
<P>
