<CENTER><H3><B>Louis N. "Woody" Jameson</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/jameson.jpg">

Woody Jameson joined King & Spalding in 1988 and was elected partner in 1995. 
<P>
He practices with the Intellectual Property and Technology group and has represented clients in a diverse range of intellectual property litigation, including a number of litigated trademark, service mark, trade dress and unfair competition cases.  He also has represented a number of clients in anti-counterfeiting litigation and litigation involving breach of intellectual property license agreements, and  infringements of copyrights and patents.
<P>
Mr. Jameson received a Bachelor of Arts degree from the University of North Carolina in 1984 and in 1988 received his law degree, magna cum laude, from the University of Georgia, where he was a member of the editorial board of the <EM>Georgia Law Review</EM>.  He is a member of the State Bar of Georgia, the American Bar Association (member, Sections on Litigation and Patent, Copyright and Trademark Law), and the Atlanta Bar Association.  Mr. Jameson is a past member of the Publications Committee for the International Trademark Association.
