<TITLE>Michael W. Johnston</TITLE>
</HEADER><body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>Michael W. Johnston</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/johnston.jpg">

Mike Johnston joined King & Spalding in 1989 as a member of the Labor, ERISA and Employment Law practice, becoming a partner in January, 1995. He is a former prosecutor whose practice has focused on labor and employment litigation for the past seven years.  He has represented management in discrimination, wrongful termination, tort, breach of contract, restrictive covenant, ERISA, OSHA, unfair labor practice and constitutional litigation.
<P>
Mr. Johnston is admitted to practice before all courts in the states of Georgia and Florida.  He is also admitted to practice before the U.S. District Courts for the Northern, Middle and Southern Districts of Georgia and the Middle District of Florida, the United States Court of Appeals for the 11th Circuit and the Court of Military Appeals. He is a member of the Labor and Employment and Litigation Sections of the American Bar Association, the Georgia Bar Association, and the Atlanta Bar Association.  Mr. Johnston also serves on the Disabilities Subcommittees of the Labor and Employment Section and the Litigation Section of the American Bar Association.  Mr. Johnston is also an adjunct faculty member for the National Institute for Trial Advocacy (<EM>NITA</EM>). <P> 

Mr. Johnston graduated from the United States Air Force Academy (with Academic Distinction) in 1975, and received his J.D. (with High Honors) from the University of Florida in 1980.  Mr. Johnston was also awarded an LL.M. in labor law from the Georgetown University Law Center in 1986. He is a member of the Order of the Coif.
<P>
