Graf Kageneck is a tax partner in the New York office of King & Spalding.
He became a partner after the merger of Kageneck & Witthuhn with King
& Spalding in 1990.
<P>
He has represented German investors in the United States for over twelve
years and currently advises U.S. investors in direct investments in
Germany.  Mr. Kageneck's practice concentrates on U.S. and German tax
planning, both inbound and outbound.
<P>
Mr. Kageneck was admitted to the Frankfurt Bar in Germany in 1976 and
to the New York Bar in 1983.  He served as a director on the boards
of several mutual funds set up by Bayerische Vereinsbank and Bank Sal.
Oppenheim.
<P>
Mr. Kageneck studied law at the Albert Ludwigs Universitat in Freiburg,
Germany, and passed his final state examinations (Assessor Examen) in
Frankfurt in 1976.  He obtained his LL.M. degree at Columbia University
in 1977.
