<TITLE>Sandra Cohen Kalter</TITLE>
</HEADER><body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>Sandra Cohen Kalter</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/kalter.jpg">

Sandra Kalter joined King & Spalding as counsel in 1992.  She represents companies on a host of food and drug issues, including drug and device approval strategies, product recalls, medical device reclassifications, over-the-counter drug review, labeling and advertising of foods, drugs, devices, and cosmetics, and the import and export of FDA-regulated products.
<P>
Ms. Kalter has also represented a variety of companies, primarily manufacturers
of FDA-regulated products, before the Federal Trade Commission and state
attorneys general in false advertising investigations.
<P>
She recently co-authored an article for the <EM>Food, Drug, Cosmetic
and Medical Device Digest </EM>on the Generic Drug Enforcement Act of 1992
and has spoken and served as a panelist at several Food and Drug Law Institute
conferences.
<P>
Ms. Kalter graduated from Northwestern University's Medill School of
Journalism in 1980 and the George Washington University Law School in
1984.  She served as Executive Articles Editor on the <EM>George Washington
Journal of International Law and Economics </EM>in 1983-84.  Prior to joining
King & Spalding, Ms. Kalter practiced law in Washington D.C. for seven
years in the food and drug and advertising areas.
<P>
