<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>John J. Kelley III</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/kelley.jpg">

J. Kelley joined King & Spalding in 1985 and was elected partner in 1992. He is a member of the Firm's Corporate Practice in the Atlanta office.
<P>
Mr. Kelley has experience in a broad range of corporate finance transactions and securities matters, particularly in the 
area of public offerings. He has represented issuers and underwriters in "shelf" registrations of investment-grade debt securities, medium-term note programs, high-yield securities offerings, and initial and secondary offerings of common stock.
<P>
He also has represented clients in connection with a variety of public and private merger and acquisition transactions, including a number of transactions involving manufacturers of agricultural and other heavy equipment. Mr. Kelley's 
practice also includes the representation of publicly-held corporations in connection with general corporate and securities compliance and reporting matters.
<P>
Mr. Kelley graduated summa cum laude from Hamilton College in 1982, where he was a member of Phi Beta Kappa. Mr. Kelley received his law degree from the University of Virginia School of Law in 1985.
