<HEADER>
<TITLE>Daniel J. King</TITLE>
</HEADER><body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>Daniel J. King</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/kingdj.jpg">

Dan King is a partner in King & Spalding's Atlanta office.  He practices
in the area of commercial litigation, with extensive experience in bankruptcy
and financial litigation.
<P>
Prior to joining the Firm in 1985, he was a commercial litigator with the firm of Jenner & Block in Chicago, Illinois.  He has had significant litigation and trial experience in a wide range of commercial litigation and bankruptcy matters.  In particular, Mr. King has been active as counsel for the Trustee in the bankruptcy of a national airline. He also has been responsible for a number of significant bankruptcy decisions in single asset real estate cases.
<P>
An active member in the American Bar Association's Section of Litigation,
Mr. King lectures in the areas of bankruptcy law and litigation
and is a contributing author to the <EM>ABA Bankruptcy Litigation Manual.</EM>
<P>
Mr. King graduated magna cum laude from the University of Illinois
School of Law in 1980, where he was a member of the <EM>Law Review </EM>and elected to the Order of the Coif.
<P>
<P>
<A HREF="/menu/bankrupt.htm">Bankruptcy & Commercial Litigation Practice</A><P>
<p><center>
<HR>
</center><p><center>
</a>
