<HEADER>
<TITLE>Jimmy F. Kirkland</TITLE>
</HEADER><body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>Jimmy F. Kirkland</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/kirkland.jpg">

Jimmy Kirkland joined King & Spalding in 1989 after serving as an engineer with the Georgia Environmental Protection Division for thirteen years. Mr. Kirkland worked in the air, hazardous waste, and chemical right to know programs at the Georgia Environmental Protection Division. He was responsible for creating and implementing the Georgia chemical reporting program under Title III of the federal superfund law. 
<P>
Mr. Kirkland holds an undergraduate degree in engineering from Georgia Tech and received his law degree in 1980. His experience as a regulator is valuable in addressing both the technical and legal aspects of environmental problems.  Since joining King & Spalding he has worked extensively in hazardous waste and ground water problems, superfund, air and water issues. He has also conducted environmental audits for a number of clients.<P>
<P>
<A HREF="/menu/envir.htm">Environmental Practice</A><P>
<p><center>
<HR>
</center><p><center>
</a>
