<HEADER>
<TITLE>W. Donald Knight, Jr.</TITLE>
</HEADER><body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>W. Donald Knight, Jr.</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/knight.jpg">
<P>
Don Knight is the senior partner in the Firm s International Practice Group.  His practice includes advising non-U.S. investors (including non-U.S. governments, companies, and high net worth individuals) with respect to structuring, negotiating and effecting investments of various kinds throughout the United States.  Such investments have included corporate acquisitions, venture capital investments, real estate investments and complex securities portfolios.  Mr. Knight has been involved in structuring and establishing numerous "off-shore" funds for U.S. investments by non-U.S. investors.  His practice also includes the establishment of structures aimed at protecting the U.S. investments of non-U.S. private and institutional clients against the adverse effects of political emergencies in a client s home country and against the adverse consequences of asset freezing or vesting actions the U.S. Government might take under the U.S. Trading With the Enemy Act and related laws during a period of political emergency.
<P>
Mr. Knight is the author of the book <EM>Structuring Foreign Investment in U.S. Real Estate </EM>(Kluwer, The Netherlands) (the book s second edition having been co-authored by Professor Richard Doernberg), and is a member of the Advisory Board of <EM>Tax Management International Journal </EM>(Washington), a Contributing Editor of <EM>INTERTAX </EM>(International Tax Review) (The Netherlands), and a member of the Advisory Board of <EM>Direct Investment in North America </EM>(London).  Mr. Knight is the author of numerous papers and articles on matters of international law and taxation and is a frequent speaker at professional seminars held in the United States and abroad.
<P>
Mr. Knight graduated with highest honors from Mississippi State University in 1961.  He received a masters degree in Comparative Literature from Emory University in 1963 and received his law degree from the University of Virginia Law School in 1967.  At the University of Virginia Law School, Mr. Knight was a member of the Editorial Board of the <EM>Virginia Law Review </EM>and a member of the Order of the Coif.
<P>
<P>
<A HREF="/menu/inter.htm">International Practice</A><P>
<p><center>
<HR>
</center><p><center><A HREF="http:/default.htm"><IMG SRC="/gif/hp.gif" ALT="[Home Page]"></A> <A HREF="http:/menu/groups.htm"><IMG SRC="/gif/pg.gif" ALT="[Practice Groups]"></A> <A HREF="http:/menu/attorn.htm"><IMG SRC="/gif/atty.gif" alt="[Attorneys]"></A><br><A HREF="http:/menu/articles.htm"><IMG SRC="/gif/art1.gif" alt="[Articles]"></A> <A HREF="http:/menu/leglink.htm"><IMG SRC="/gif/lr.gif" alt="[Legal Resources]"></A> <A HREF="http:/menu/recruit.htm"><IMG SRC="/gif/recruit.jpg" ALT="Recruiting"></A></center>
