<TITLE>C. Thomas Kruse</TITLE>
</HEADER><body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>C. Thomas Kruse</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/kruse.jpg">
<P>
Tom Kruse joined the Firm's Houston office in 1995 to work in the Litigation Practice as counsel. He came to King & Spalding from McDade & Fogler in Houston, where he practiced commercial litigation focusing on contract and other disputes for oil and gas companies.
<P>
Mr. Kruse worked as a law clerk for The Honorable Ricardo Hinojosa, United States District Court Judge for the Southern District of Texas, during 1989-1990. After his clerkship, he joined Fulbright & Jaworski as an associate where he practiced until leaving to open McDade & Fogler, where he became a partner in 1994. His litigation experience includes all aspects of trial and appellate practice, including dealing with pretrial and discovery issues in complex cases. He has handled matters for a variety of national and Houston-based clients.
<P>
He received his undergraduate degree from Emory University in 1985. After studying at the University of St. Andrews, Scotland, for a year, Mr. Kruse attended Vanderbilt University Law School and received his law degree in 1989.
<P>
