<TITLE>Steven R. Lainoff</TITLE>
</HEADER><body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>Steven R. Lainoff</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/lainoff.jpg">

Steve Lainoff joined King & Spalding in 1991 as a partner in the Washington, D.C. office.  He represents clients in a broad range of international tax
matters, with particular emphasis on joint ventures, transfer pricing
planning and controversies and financing transactions.
<P>
Prior to joining King & Spalding, Mr. Lainoff served as Associate Chief Counsel (International) of the Internal Revenue Service and the International Tax Counsel of the Treasury Department - the two highest positions for international tax lawyers in the Federal government.  He speaks and writes on international tax issues, and is the co-author of an extensive article on foreign joint ventures published in the <EM>Tax Law Review.</EM>
<P>
Mr. Lainoff received his undergraduate degree from Boston University
in 1974.  He received his law degree With Highest Distinction from the
University of Arizona in 1977 and was a member of the Order of the Coif,
and received his LL.M. in Taxation from New York University in 1978.
<P>
<P>
