<HR>
<CENTER>
<H3><B>George H. Lanier</B></H3></CENTER><IMG
ALIGN="LEFT" VSPACE="10" HSPACE="10" SRC="/gif/lanier.jpg">
<P>George Lanier is a partner in the Trusts and Estates Practice.  He joined
the Atlanta office of King &amp; Spalding in 1970 and became a partner in 1976.</P>
<P>His practice covers the full range of trusts and estates matters, with a
particular emphasis on planning for charitable giving and tax-exempt
organizations.  Mr. Lanier has principal responsibility for the Firm's
representation of some of the Southeast's largest and most active foundations as
well as for many of the schools, universities, foundations supporting state
universities and other exempt organizations the Firm represents.  Among other
recent transactions, he handled, for a consortium of private foundations, the
creation of one of the country's largest supporting organizations to support a
Southeastern university</P>
<P>Mr. Lanier is a member of the American Bar Association's Section of Real
Property, Probate and Trust Law, and served as the Chairman of Nonprofit
Corporation Code Revision Committee for the State Bar of Georgia.  He is a
frequent lecturer and panel member at tax institutes, conferences and other
continuing legal education programs.  He is active with a number of charitable
and cultural institutions and has served on the governing boards of several,
including United Way of Metropolitan Atlanta, the Metropolitan Atlanta Community
Foundation, the Atlanta Symphony Orchestra and two private foundations.</P>
<P>He received a B.A., cum laude, in 1966 from Harvard University and a J.D. in
1970 from Columbia University Law School.</P>
<P><A HREF="/menu/trusts.htm">Trusts &amp; Estates Practice</A></P>
