<TITLE>Jackie S. Levinson</TITLE>
</HEADER><body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>Jackie S. Levinson</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/levinson.jpg">

Jackie Levinson has been a partner in the Washington, D.C. Tax Practice of King
& Spalding since 1985.  She joined the Firm in 1983.
<P>
Ms. Levinson has a wide range of practice experience, including tax
controversy work, tax planning involving complex partnership structures,
bilateral income tax treaties, U.S. taxation of multinational corporations,
financial instruments, leveraged lease transactions, tax indemnification
agreements, and unrelated business taxable income for tax-exempt organizations,
and tax legislation.
<P>
Before joining the Firm, Ms. Levinson served as attorney-advisor, Associate
Tax Legislative Counsel, and Deputy Tax Legislative Counsel in the Office
of Tax Legislative Counsel under the U.S. Treasury Assistant Secretary
for Tax Policy.  She began her career in private practice in New York
City.
<P>
Ms. Levinson received her undergraduate degree magna cum laude from
Vassar College in 1969 and her law degree from Yale University in 1972.
<P>
