<HEADER>
<TITLE>Ralph B. Levy</TITLE>
</HEADER><body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>Ralph B. Levy</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/levy.jpg">

Ralph Levy, Managing Partner of King & Spalding, is a bankruptcy and commercial litigator.  He joined the Firm as an associate in 1974 and was admitted to the partnership in 1979.
<P>
Throughout his 20-year career at the Firm, Mr. Levy has served clients in a broad range of financially-oriented litigation, representing national firms of accountants and actuaries in professional malpractice and securities cases, major financial institutions in bankruptcy, lender liability and other commercial cases, and corporate and partnership taxpayers in disputes with the IRS. 
<P>
To strengthen the litigation component of the Firm's bankruptcy and creditors  rights practice, particularly in contested bankruptcy hearings on valuation, cram-down, relief from stay, and cash collateral disputes, Mr. Levy joined the Firm's Bankruptcy and Commercial Litigation Group, where his practice has become even more focused on the litigation side of representing lender clients in bankruptcy and other insolvency related disputes.  This recent internal reorganization, which consolidates substantive bankruptcy experience with pre-trial discovery and trial expertise, permits the Firm to consistently bring to bear on bankruptcy matters the same level of litigation planning and execution skills that are afforded to non-bankruptcy litigation representations. 
<P>
Mr. Levy is a member of the International Society of Barristers and has taught advanced litigation skills as a member of the visiting faculty for Emory Law School's Masters of Litigation program.
<P>
In 1970, he received his J.D., cum laude, from the University of Pennsylvania Law School, where he also was awarded the Order of the Coif.  He has served as a military trial lawyer and judge in the U.S. Navy JAGC (1971-1974; Navy Commendation Medal).<P>
<P>
<A HREF="/menu/bankrupt.htm">Bankruptcy & Commercial Litigation Practice</A><P>
