<TITLE>Hector E. Llorens, Jr.</TITLE>
</HEADER><body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>Hector E. Llorens, Jr.</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/llorens.jpg">

Hector Llorens is a partner in the Banking and Finance Practice Group of King & Spalding's Atlanta Office. Mr. Llorens' practice focuses on debt financings, including secured and unsecured credit facilities, inventory and receivables financing, recapitalizations, leverage buyouts and acquisition financing, mezzanine financing, structured finance, securitizations and debtor-in-possession financing.  His practice includes the representation of foreign and domestic lenders, as well as borrowers.
<P>
Mr. Llorens joined King & Spalding in 1987 and was elected a partner in 1994.  He received his law degree in 1986 from Columbia University, where he served as Associate Editor of the Columbia Journal of Law and Social Problems.  From 1986-1987, he served as Law Clerk to the Hon. Robert S. Vance, U.S. Court of Appeals, Eleventh Circuit. <P>
