<HEADER>
<TITLE>L. Joseph Loveland</TITLE>
</HEADER><body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>L. Joseph Loveland</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/loveland.jpg">

Joe Loveland is a partner in the Litigation Practice Group of King & Spalding's Houston office. Mr. Loveland's practice focuses on civil litigation. He has trial experience in commercial fraud, breach of contract, trade secret, trademark, and distributor termination matters. He has also handled class action and multi-plaintiff actions in the antitrust, securities, and toxic tort fields.
<P>
Mr. Loveland's recent trial experience includes:
<P>
<UL>
<LI>Representation of a large corporate client in a two-week jury trial against its international apparel licensee for breach of contract and breach of a credit agreement and in defense of counterclaims for breach of contract and fraud.<P>
</ul>
<ul>
<LI>Defense of a hospital on claims of breach of contract and misappropriation of trade secrets involving computerized hospital information systems in a three-week trial.<P>

<LI>Defense, in two separate trials and appeals, of a group of United States and Netherlands Antilles corporations against corporate alter ego and fraudulent conveyance claims brought by a German construction company. <P>

<LI>Representation of a multi-national bank in a variety of matters in state and federal courts arising out of the $2 billion of unauthorized loans by the bank's Atlanta branch to the government of Iraq.
</UL>
<P>
Mr. Loveland graduated cum laude from Harvard Law School. He joined King & Spalding in 1976 and was elected partner in 1983. He has served as the partner in charge of the Firm's Houston office since it was founded in 1995. 
<P>
