Bill Lummus is a partner in King & Spalding's Atlanta office and a member of the Commercial Litigation Practice.  He joined the Firm in 1986 and was elected partner in 1994. Mr. Lummus' practice encompasses a broad range of commercial litigation matters, with emphasis on contractual disputes, franchise and dealership law, and shareholder and fiduciary litigation.
