<HEADER>
<TITLE>Charles K. McKnight, Jr.</TITLE>
</HEADER><body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>Charles K. McKnight, Jr.</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/mcknight.jpg">

Charles McKnight is a member of King & Spalding's Litigation Practice, focusing on commercial litigation and special investigations.  He joined the Firm's Atlanta office in 1987 and became a partner in 1994.
<P>
Mr. McKnight has acted as defense counsel in a variety of cases in litigation, arbitration, and mediation, including cases alleging breach of contract, tortious interference with business relations, violations of the Voting Rights Act, director and officer liability, and securities law violations.<P>

A participant in a variety of civic activities, Mr. McKnight is a member of the Board of Directors of the American Diabetes Association Georgia Affiliate and of the Board of Directors of the Northern District of Georgia Civil Litigation Fund.
<P>
Mr. McKnight graduated from Emory University with a B.A. degree in 1982.  He attended Vanderbilt University School of Law, where he served as Student Writing Editor of the <EM>Vanderbilt Law Review </EM>and was elected to membership in the Order of the Coif.  Following law school, he worked as law clerk to the Honorable Richard C. Freeman of the United States District Court for the Northern District of Georgia.
<P>
<P>
<A HREF="/menu/comlit.htm">Commercial Litigation Practice</A><P>
