<HEADER>
<TITLE>Kathrine A. McLendon</TITLE>
</HEADER><body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>Kathrine A. McLendon</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/mclendon.jpg">

Kathrine McLendon is a member of King & Spalding's Bankruptcy and Commercial
Litigation Group in New York.  She joined the Firm in 1990 and became
a partner in 1991.
<P>
Prior to joining King & Spalding, she practiced in the bankruptcy department
at Simpson Thacher & Bartlett in New York.
<P>
Ms. McLendon has focused her practice on bankruptcy and creditors'
rights since 1983, with an emphasis on institutional creditor representation
in Chapter 11 reorganizations and out-of-court restructurings.  Particular
areas of concentration in her practice include commercial real estate, airlines and utilities.
<P>
Ms. McLendon is the Chair of the Subcommittee on Bankruptcy Aspects
of Business Transactions of the Business Bankruptcy Committee of the
ABA Business Law Section.  In addition, she serves as the Chair of the
Task Force on Project Finance and Leveraged Leasing.  She is a contributing
editor of <EM>Norton Bankruptcy Law & Practice </EM>and lectures on
bankruptcy topics.
<P>
Ms. McLendon received her undergraduate degree, magna cum laude, from Davidson College in 1977 where she was Phi Beta Kappa. She received her law degree with high honors from the University of North Carolina in 1980 where she was a member of the <EM>North Carolina Law Review </EM>and the Order of the Coif. She is admitted to practice in New York, Georgia and North Carolina.
<P>
<P>
