<HEADER>
<TITLE>Martin M. McNerney</TITLE>
</HEADER><body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>Martin M. McNerney</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/mcnerney.jpg">

Marty McNerney joined King & Spalding's Washington, D.C. office in 1994.
His practice concentrates in international trade remedy actions and
litigation.  He has extensive experience in prosecuting antidumping,
countervailing duty, and Section 337 cases before the International
Trade Commission, the Department of Commerce and the U.S. Court of International
Trade.  His civil litigation practice also includes representing policyholders
in casualty insurance coverage disputes and representing defendants
in product liability claims.
<P>
Mr. McNerney is a member of the International Trade Section of the
District of Columbia Bar Association.  He is admitted to practice before
the U.S. District Court for the District of Columbia, the U.S. District
Court for the District of Maryland, the United States Court of International
Trade, and the United States Courts of Appeals for the Fourth, Fifth,
Sixth, District of Columbia, and Federal Circuits.  He has handled litigation
matters before all of these courts.
<P>
Mr. McNerney earned his J.D. degree from the University of Virginia
in 1980.  While in law school, he served on the Editorial Board of the
<EM>Virginia Law Review, </EM>was a Dillard Fellow legal writing instructor and
was elected to the Raven Society.  He graduated magna cum laude from
Hampden-Sydney College in 1977, where he was elected Phi Beta Kappa
and Omicron Delta Kappa and was captain of the basketball team.
<P>
<P>
