<TITLE>John Hays Mershon</TITLE>
</HEADER><body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>John Hays Mershon</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/mershon.jpg">

Hays Mershon is a partner in King & Spalding's Banking and Finance Practice Group, concentrating in corporate lending for leveraged buyouts, recapitalizations, debt restructurings and debt refinancings.
<P>
His clients in this practice have included the Southeast regional offices of money center banks, international banks and non-bank financial institutions.  The transactions that he has closed for these clients include financing for the start-up of a major cable network, leveraged buyout financings provided for the acquisition of divisions of numerous large companies, and financing provided for the "going private" acquisition of a diversified Los Angeles-based holding company.
<P>
Mr. Mershon is a member of the Atlanta and American Bar Associations and the State Bar of Georgia.  His civic activities include service on the Board of Directors of the Academy Theatre Company, the Board of Directors and Executive Committee of the Alliance Theatre Company, and the Board of Trustees of the Atlanta Botanical Garden.
<P>
Mr. Mershon received his B.A. degree in 1968 and his law degree in 1971, both from the University of Virginia.  While in law school, he served on the Managing Board of Editors of the <EM>Virginia Law Review </EM>and was a member of the Order of the Coif.
<P>
