<TITLE>Robert W. Miller</TITLE>
</HEADER><body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>Robert W. Miller</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/millerr.jpg">

Bob Miller has represented healthcare clients in a variety of corporate
finance transactions, including mergers and acquisitions involving more
than 75 hospitals, debt and equity securities offerings, private placements,
debt and equity restructurings and other corporate finance transactions.
These representations have involved work in related areas, including
Medicare, licensure and certificate of need law and federal antitrust
law.
<P>
Mr. Miller has served as President of the American Academy of Hospital
Attorneys, President of the Georgia Academy of Hospital Attorneys and
a member of the Governing Board of the Health Law Forum of the American
Bar Association.  He has also served on the American Bar Association
Committee on Federal Regulation of Securities and an American Hospital
Association Task Force on Antitrust Policy.  He has lectured at seminars
for the American Academy of Hospitals Attorneys, National Health Lawyers
Association, American College of Legal Medicine and ABA Health Law Forum.
<P>
Mr. Miller's civic activities include past service as a member of the
Board of Directors of the University of Georgia Athletic Association
and of the Executive Committee of the Yale Law School Association.
<P>
A magna cum laude graduate of the University of Georgia in 1964, Mr.
Miller received his law degree from Yale University Law School in 1967,
where he was awarded the Gallagher Jury Trial Prize.
<P>
