<HEADER>
<TITLE>William F. Nelson</TITLE>
</HEADER><body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>William F. Nelson</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/nelsonw.jpg">

William Nelson joined the Tax Practice of King & Spalding in 1972 and was elected partner in 1978.  From 1986 until 1988, Mr. Nelson served as Chief Counsel for the Internal Revenue Service, returning to the
Firm at the end of his appointment.
<P>
He is co-author of the four-volume treatise: <EM>Federal Taxation of Partnerships
and Partners, </EM>(Warren, Gorham & Lamont, 2d ed., 1990), and also co-authored
<EM>Federal Taxation of Partnerships and Partners: Structuring and Drafting
Agreements </EM>(Warren Gorham & Lamont, 2d ed., 1993). Mr. Nelson has written
numerous articles on tax law for various journals, including <EM>The Tax
Law Review, Taxes, </EM>and <EM>The Virginia Tax Review.</EM>
<P>
Mr. Nelson has spoken at various tax institutes,
including the New York University Tax Institute, the University of Southern
California Tax Institute, the University of Chicago Tax Institute, the
University of Texas Tax Institute, the University of Virginia Tax Institute,
the Southern Federal Tax Institute, the New England Tax Institute, the
Tax Executives' Institute, the American Law Institute/American Bar Association
and the Practicing Law Institute.
<P>
He is a graduate of Mississippi State University (highest honors, 1969)
and of the University of Virginia School of Law (1972).  While at the
University of Virginia, Mr. Nelson was Editor-in-Chief of the <EM>Virginia
Law Review </EM>and was named to the Order of the Coif.  He is a member of
the American College of Tax Counsel.
<P>
<P>
