<HEADER>
<TITLE>Floyd C. Newton III</TITLE>
</HEADER><body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>Floyd C. Newton III</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/newton.jpg">

Floyd Newton joined King & Spalding in 1980 and has served as bond
counsel, underwriters' counsel and special tax counsel on a wide variety
of public finance matters.  He was elected a partner in 1987.
<P>
Mr. Newton has extensive experience in the financing by utility companies
and other private companies of pollution control and sewage and solid
waste disposal facilities, and the financing by governmental and nonprofit
corporations of healthcare facilities.  He also has worked on a wide
variety of governmental and education financings.  Mr. Newton has also
served as special tax counsel on a variety of transactions, including
current and advance refunding issues.
<P>
Mr. Newton is a member of the American Bar Association and the National
Association of Bond Lawyers.  He is a member of the Board of Directors
of the National Association of Bond Lawyers and the Chairman of the
Bond Attorneys Workshop.  He has appeared as a speaker at numerous seminars
and workshops on various tax exempt financing topics.
<P>
Originally from Griffin, Georgia, Mr. Newton graduated from Princeton
University magna cum laude in 1977 with a degree in economics and received
his Juris Doctor degree magna cum laude from the University of Georgia
School of Law in 1980.  While in law school, Mr. Newton was on the Editorial
Board of the <EM>Georgia Law Review </EM>and served as Executive Editor of the
<EM>Georgia Law Review </EM>in his final year.  He was also a member of the Order
of the Coif.
<P>
<P>
<A HREF="/menu/pubfin.htm">Public Finance Practice</A><P>
<p><center>
<HR>
</center><p><center>
</a>
