<TITLE>Michael E. Norton</TITLE>
</HEADER><body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>Michael E. Norton</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/norton.jpg">

Michael Norton is a partner in the New York office of King & Spalding.  He practices in the area of commercial litigation, with a focus on bankruptcy, financial and banking matters.
<P>
Prior to joining King & Spalding, Mr. Norton served as an Assistant United States Attorney for the Southern District of New York, in that office's Criminal Division.  He has significant litigation and trial experience in a wide range of commercial litigation, bankruptcy and criminal matters.  He regularly represents clients in federal, state and bankruptcy court and before federal regulatory agencies and grand juries.
<P>
Mr. Norton is an active member of the Association of the Bar of the City of New York and of the New York County Lawyers  Association where he is a member of the Business Bankruptcy Committee.
<P>
In 1975, he graduated from the Columbia University Law School, where he was Articles Editor of the <EM>Columbia Law Review</EM> and a Harlan Fiske Stone Scholar.
<P>
<P>
<A HREF="/menu/comlit.htm">Commercial Litigation Practice</A><P>
