<HEADER>
<TITLE>Les Oakes</TITLE>
</HEADER><body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>Les Oakes</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/oakes.jpg">

Les Oakes joined King & Spalding's Environmental Practice in 1986 following a career of over eleven years as an environmental engineer with the Environmental Protection Division, Georgia Department of Natural Resources.
<P>
During his service with the State of Georgia, Mr. Oakes gained valuable
experience in permitting and enforcement actions and did extensive work
in air and water pollution and hazardous waste.  His background as a
regulator and engineer is particularly useful in audits and in developing
practical ways to address environmental concerns.  Mr. Oakes also has
directed and conducted the environmental due diligence portions of a
number of complex transactions involving industrial facilities and properties.
<P>
Mr. Oakes holds an engineering degree and a masters degree from Georgia
Tech and received his law degree from Georgia State University.
<P>
