<HEADER>
<TITLE>Margaret E. O'Neil</TITLE>
</HEADER><body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>Margaret E. O'Neil</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/oneil.jpg">

Margaret O'Neil is a partner in the Banking and Finance Group of King & Spalding s New York office.  She represents banks and other financial institutions in a wide variety of commercial lending transactions.  Ms. O'Neil has been particularly active in the project finance area, and has represented lenders in connection with electric power generation and chemical production facilities and, more recently, infrastructure projects, such as privatized toll roads.  Ms. O'Neil also regularly represents lenders to electric utilities, among other corporate borrowers.  
<P>
She has served as lead counsel to numerous bank groups in connection with conventional secured and unsecured credit facilities, as well as more innovative structured financings.  In addition to representing lenders, Ms. O'Neil also advises project developers in structuring and developing electric and other industrial projects.
<P>
Ms. O'Neil became a member of the Firm in 1992, upon the merger of the New York law firm of Porter & Travers with King & Spalding.  Ms. O'Neil joined Porter & Travers in 1987 as an associate, and was elected to partnership in 1990.
<P>
Ms. O'Neil received her undergraduate degree from Wellesley College in 1977.  Ms. O'Neil graduated cum laude from Georgetown University Law Center in 1983, where she was an associate editor of <EM>The Tax Lawyer</EM>.  Ms. O'Neil is a member of the New York State and The District of Columbia bars.
<P>
<P>
<A HREF="/menu/bankfin.htm">Banking & Finance Practice </A><P>
