<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>Robert G. Pennington</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/penningt.jpg">

Bob Pennington joined King & Spalding in 1984 and was elected partner
in 1989.  His practice involves representation of domestic and foreign
investors, developers and lenders in the acquisition, development, leasing,
financing and sale of commercial properties.
<P>
Mr. Pennington began his practice in 1981 after graduating from Emory
University with his Juris Doctor and Master of Business Administration
degrees.  In 1976 he received his Bachelor of Arts degree, with honors
in psychology, from Emory University.  While at Emory Law School, Mr.
Pennington served as the Managing Editor of <EM>Annual Survey of Bankruptcy
Law </EM>(1980-1981).  He lectures at professional seminars
and continuing legal education programs.
