<HEADER>
<TITLE>Michael W. Perrin</TITLE>
</HEADER><body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>Michael W. Perrin</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/perrin.jpg">

Michael Perrin is a litigation partner in King & Spalding's Houston office.  Mr. Perrin has maintained a broad based litigation practice throughout Texas since 1972.  He has tried cases in Federal and State courts, including a wide range of personal injury actions arising from oil field activities, transportation, and industrial plants.  In addition, he has handled cases involving mineral leases, contract disputes, and insurance matters.  
<P>
Significant cases include:

<P>
<UL><LI>Prosecution of a wrongful death case arising from an underground utilities construction project in Eagle Pass, Texas.  Legal issues involved respective contractual rights and duties between the owner, general contractor, subcontractor, and employees, cross indemnification, governmental immunity, and insurance coverages.
<P>
<LI>Prosecution of a class action on behalf of royalty owners for underpayment of royalties owed under the applicable price schedules.  Complex factual issues involved measurement of volumes of gas production over time, and application of contractual price escalation clauses to that production over time.
<P>
<LI>Prosecution of product liability cases involving electrical transformers and multi-piece truck wheels.
<P>
<LI>Prosecution of technical negligence cases involving oil field drilling equipment, production facilities, and hydrogen sulpfide facilities.
</UL><P>
Mr. Perrin is a member of the American College of Trial Lawyers, International Academy of Trial Lawyers (State Chair 1994-Present) and the International Society of Barristers (Board of Directors, 1995-Present).  He is a graduate of the University of Texas and University of Texas School of Law.<P>
<A HREF="/menu/comlit.htm">Commercial Litigation Practice</A><P>
