<HEADER>
<TITLE>Eugene M. Pfeifer</TITLE>
</HEADER><body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>Eugene M. Pfeifer</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/pfeifer.jpg">

Gene Pfeifer joined King & Spalding as a partner in 1986 and is head of the Food and Drug Practice Group.
<P>
He served for a year in the General Counsel's office of the Federal Trade Commission and ten years in the Chief Counsel's Office at FDA as Associate Chief Counsel for Enforcement, Associate Chief Counsel for Drugs, and Deputy Chief Counsel for Regulations and Hearings.  During his ten years at FDA, he was frequently the agency's lead litigator; with one exception, he briefed all of the FDA's cases before the Supreme Court in the 1970s.
<P>
When Mr. Pfeifer entered private practice, he undertook representation
of the Generic Pharmaceutical Industry Association (GPIA), a trade association
of generic drug manufacturers.  As counsel to GPIA, Mr. Pfeifer was
a major participant in the development of the Drug Price Competition
and Patent Term Restoration Act of 1984 and is now one of the leading
authorities on the subject.
<P>
He is also counsel to the National Pharmaceutical Alliance, an association
of 160 primarily small generic drug manufacturers, distributors, and
branded distributors, and he represents numerous individual companies.
<P>
Mr. Pfeifer is a graduate of Brown University and the Georgetown University
Law Center (1967).
<P>
<P>
<A HREF="/menu/food.htm">Food & Drug Practice</A><P>
<p><center>
