<HEADER>
<TITLE>Glen A. Reed</TITLE>
</HEADER><body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>Glen A. Reed</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/reed.jpg">

Glen Reed currently chairs King & Spalding's Healthcare Practice Group.    His practice concentrates on the general representation of healthcare systems, and on specialized projects involving healthcare industry restructuring, reimbursement, fraud and abuse, antitrust, managed care, and new service development.
<P>
Mr. Reed serves as a director and President-Elect of the American Academy of Healthcare Attorneys. He was the legal consultant to the Georgia Governor's Commission on Health Care. He is a member of the advisory board of the Emory
University School of Public Health, and he is a member of the National Health Lawyers Association and the Medical Group Management Association.  Mr. Reed has served as President of the Georgia Academy of Hospital Attorneys and as Chair of the Committee on Medicare Fraud and Abuse Safe Harbors of the American Academy of Healthcare Attorneys. He has served as Chairman of the board of Visiting Nurse Health System, Inc., and the Atlanta Advisory Board of CARE, and as President of the Atlanta Alliance on Developmental Disabilities.
<P>
Mr. Reed has lectured extensively on healthcare industry legal matters, and
served for six years as chair of the annual seminar <EM>Fundamentals of Healthcare Law.  </EM>Mr. Reed has been listed in the publications <EM>The Best Lawyers
in America </EM>and <EM>Who's Who in America</EM>.  He is a graduate of the University of Tennessee and the Yale Law School.
<P>
<P>
<A HREF="/menu/health.htm">Healthcare Practice</A><P>
<p><center>
<HR>
</center><p><center>
</a>
</A></center><P><center>
