<HEADER>
<TITLE>Russell B. Richards</TITLE>
</HEADER><body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>Russell B. Richards</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/richards.jpg">

Russ Richards joined King & Spalding in 1974. His practice focuses on the representation of purchasers and sellers in connection with the acquisition and sale of publicly-held and privately-owned companies, in the representation of companies establishing domestic and international joint ventures and in the representation of companies in connection with financing transactions (such as public debt offerings and leveraged lease transactions). 
<P>
His practice has included transactions throughout the United States and in Canada, Mexico, South America, the United Kingdom and Continental Europe. He has represented several New York Stock Exchange-listed companies in connection with acquisitions and divestitures of foreign and domestic corporations in connection with domestic and international joint ventures. He also serves as counsel to a major airline in connection with public debt offerings and aircraft sale-leaseback transactions.<P>
Mr. Richards' background in transactions, accounting (he has passed the National Examination for Certified Public Accountants) and sales has provided him with significant knowledge and skills in analyzing, structuring and negotiating domestic and international business transactions.  <P>
<P>
