<HEADER>
<TITLE>Dvorah A. Richman</TITLE>
</HEADER><body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>Dvorah A. Richman</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/richman.jpg">

Dvorah Richman joined King & Spalding in 1990, and is a partner in the Firm's Washington, D.C. Food & Drug Practice Group. 
<P>
She has practiced in the field for more than a dozen years, and has dealt with diverse matters such as FDA's regulation of food additives, Drug Enforcement Administration issues, Lanham Act matters and California's Proposition 65; in both administrative and litigation contexts.
<P>
Ms. Richman focuses her practice in the area of medical devices.  She represents medical device manufacturers in a wide variety of regulatory and enforcement matters, including those relating to import-export, good manufacturing practices, promotion issues, product recalls, and product applications.  She has written and lectured on FDA-related issues for the Food and Drug Law Institute ("FDLI"), the Health Industry Manufacturers Association ("HIMA"), and the Regulatory Affairs Professionals Society ("RAPS").  These presentations include FDLI's Basic Device Law Course, and numerous speeches concerning topics such as promotion and advertising, product export, illegal actions by FDA, and product approvals.  
<P>
Prior to becoming an attorney, Ms. Richman served as a budget/legislative analyst for the Joint Budget Committee, Colorado State Legislature.  Ms. Richman was also a practicing speech pathologist and director of speech pathology services for Denver Head Start, having earned Masters and Bachelors degrees in speech pathology from the University of Denver and Arizona State University, respectively.
<P>
Ms. Richman received her J.D. degree from the Columbus School of Law, Catholic University of America where she worked on the <EM>Food, Drug, Cosmetic Law Journal.</EM><P>
<A HREF="/menu/food.htm">Food & Drug Practice</A><P>
