<HEAD>
<TITLE>William G. Roche</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#00009c" VLINK="#8e2323">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER></CENTER>
<HR>
<CENTER>
<H3><B>William G. Roche</B></H3></CENTER><IMG
ALIGN="LEFT" VSPACE="10" HSPACE="10" SRC="/gif/roche.jpg">
<P>Bill Roche joined King &amp; Spalding in 1983 and became a partner in 1991.
He is a member of the Firm's Intellectual Property and Technology Practice Group
in Atlanta.  Mr. Roche received his law degree from Stanford University in 1983,
graduated with highest honors and was a member of the Order of the Coif. </P>
<P>He has represented clients in connection with a variety of merger and
acquisition transactions involving intellectual property and technology-based
assets. He also advises clients in connection with the acquisition, development,
marketing and protection of intellectual property and technology assets through
development agreements, licensing, joint ventures and other arrangements.  Mr.
Roche's practice is focused primarily on the computer software and
telecommunications industries.</P>
<P>Selected recent transactions include:</P>
<UL>
<LI> Assisting a large telecommunications company in connection with the
formation of its national PCS joint venture, including formation of a joint
venture to own and operate the nation's first operational PCS network in
Washington, D.C., and the development and negotiation of affiliation
arrangements between the joint venture and other PCS license holders who will
affiliate with the national PCS network.
<P></P></LI>
<LI> Representation of a developer of software which provides the principal
functionality in telecommunications handsets and basestations for the wireless,
satellite and broadband network communications markets, including preparation
for an initial public offering and a private placement of $10 million to
institutional investors.
<P></P></LI>
<LI> Negotiation of systems integration/software development agreements on
behalf of a large systems integration client, including negotiation of a joint
venture with a large German company to perform systems integration work in
Europe, and negotiation of the joint venture's software development agreement
and license with a German cellular telecommunications company.
<P></P></LI>
<LI> General representation of a number of other privately held software
developers in connection with their general business matters, including joint
development and joint marketing arrangements, reseller and other distribution
arrangements, export control issues and capital raising activities.
<P></P></LI>
<LI> General representation of a company which produces multimedia CD-ROM
software products for consumer and education markets in connection with all
aspects of its business, including distribution, co-development, content
licensing and other arrangements, venture capital investments and completion of
the company's initial public offering within the last year.
<P></P></LI>
<LI> Acquisitions of numerous software companies, including companies based in
Europe.
</LI></UL>
<P><A HREF="/menu/ipt.htm">Intellectual Property &amp; Technology Practice</A></P>
