<HEADER>
<TITLE>Brian Rosner</TITLE>
</HEADER><body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>Brian Rosner</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/rosner.jpg">

Brian Rosner is a partner in the Firm's New York Litigation Practice, where
he concentrates in complex commercial litigation, internal corporate
investigations and white-collar defense work.  He regularly represents
clients in state and federal court, and before federal regulatory agencies,
and has been retained to arbitrate complex commercial matters.
<P>
Prior to entering private practice, Mr. Rosner was the senior trial
attorney in the Frauds Bureau of the New York County District Attorney's
Office, where he practiced from 1975 through 1988.  Several of his more
noteworthy trials and appellate cases are recounted in his book, <EM>Swindle,</EM>
published in 1990.  Mr. Rosner has lectured before professional
groups on fraud and complex litigation.
<P>
Mr. Rosner is active in the Association of the Bar of the City of New
York, where he is a member of the Judiciary Committee and panel responsible
for mediating disciplinary complaints brought against attorneys.
<P>
Mr. Rosner received his undergraduate training at the London School
of Economics and Columbia College, where he graduated magna cum laude
in 1972.  He received his law degree in 1975 from the Columbia University
Law School, where he was the editor-in-chief of the <EM>Columbia Journal
of Law and Social Problems</EM>.
<P>
<P>
