<HEADER>
<TITLE>Michael Eric Ross</TITLE>
</HEADER><body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>Michael Eric Ross</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/ross.jpg">

Mickey Ross joined King & Spalding in 1974 and was elected partner in
1980.  His practice focuses on litigation, primarily in the areas of
labor and employment, ERISA, antitrust and trade regulation and general
commercial disputes.
<P>
Among the cases he has successfully defended were as follows:
<UL>
<LI>the first alleged class action under the Workers Adjustment and Retraining Notification ("<EM>WARN</EM>") Act;
<LI>a challenge by osteopaths to a hospital bylaw limiting its medical staff to physicians who have completed a post-graduate training program approved by the Accreditation Council for Graduate Medical Education; and 
<LI>a claim by minority shareholders in a tender offer that the majority shareholder breached his fiduciary duties by selling his controlling interest for a premium.

</UL>
<P>
Mr. Ross has published numerous articles since 1980 including the
annual antitrust survey of the Eleventh Circuit in the <EM>Mercer Law Review. </EM>In addition, he speaks on various employment law issuesand developments, including the Americans With Disabilities Act, the Family and Medical Leave Act of 1993, sexual harassment, and restrictive covenants in employment agreements.
<P>
He is a member of the American Bar Association, the Atlanta Bar Association
and the State Bar of Georgia, in which he was elected Chairman of its
Antitrust Section in 1994.
<P>
Mr. Ross was the valedictorian of his graduating class at the University
of Florida.  He received his law degree magna cum laude from Harvard
University, where he was invited to join the <EM>Harvard Law Review.  </EM>Mr.
Ross was also a Rhodes Scholar nominee from the State of Florida.
<P>
<P>
<A HREF="/menu/labor.htm">Labor, ERISA & Employment Practice</A><P>
