<TITLE>Michael C. Russ</TITLE>
</HEADER><body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>Michael C. Russ</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/russ.jpg">

A partner in the General Litigation Department, Mike Russ practiced for two years in Washington, D.C. and joined King & Spalding in 1971.  He was elected partner in 1975.  His practice focuses in contract disputes, SEC and tax investigations, as well as securities and general commercial disputes.
<P>
Mr. Russ is a Fellow of the American College of Trial Lawyers, and member of the litigation, taxation and business law sections of the American Bar Association. He also is a member of the State Bar of Georgia, the District of Columbia Bar and the Atlanta Bar Association.<P>

Mr. Russ graduated Order of the Coif from Duke University School of Law in 1969 where he was Note Editor of the <EM>Duke Law Journal</EM>.  He obtained his B.A. from Duke with a major in economics in 1966.
<P>
Mr. Russ has served as a Trustee of the Metropolitan Atlanta Crime Commission and a board member of Ministries to Women, a home for battered women and their children.  He has served as a member of the Youth Committee of the First Presbyterian Church of Atlanta.
<P>
