<TITLE>Isam Salah</TITLE>
</HEADER><body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>Isam Salah</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/salah.jpg">

Isam Salah is a partner in King & Spalding's Banking and Finance Practice Group in New York. He was in private practice in New York and overseas before joining the Firm as a partner in 1992.
<P>
Mr. Salah focuses his practice on domestic and international financial transactions, with particular emphasis on the representation of foreign banks in the United States, structured trade finance transactions and transactions involving LDC debt.
<P>
He graduated from Case Western Reserve University in 1973. He received his law degree in 1976 from Cleveland State University, where he served as Editor-in-Chief of the <EM>Cleveland State Law Review.</EM> Mr. Salah received an advanced law degree from Georgetown University in 1976 after a two year fellowship at the University's International Law Center.
<P>
<P>
