Bess Schachner joined King & Spalding in 1987 as a member of the Banking and Finance Practice in the Atlanta office.  Her practice focuses on a variety of financial transactions, with an emphasis on lender representation in connection with secured and unsecured corporate loans.
<P>
Ms. Schachner received her J.D., summa cum laude, in 1986 from the University of Georgia, where she was a member of the Editorial Board of the <EM>Georgia Law Review</EM> (1984-85).  She earned her B.A., magna cum laude, from Emory University in 1983 and is a member of Phi Beta Kappa and the Order of the Coif.
