<CENTER><H3><B>Richard A. Schneider</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/schneidr.jpg">

Doc Schneider is a litigation partner in the Atlanta office of King & Spalding.  He joined the Firm in 1981 and became a partner in 1988. He focuses his practice on litigation and special investigations. Mr. Schneider has acted as defense counsel in a variety of cases, including cases alleging product liability, employment discrimination, toxic torts, interference with television broadcasting rights, and letter of credit violations. Mr. Schneider also served as plaintiff's counsel in a two-year breach of contract action brought by two consumers against a California based company.
<P>
An active member in a number of civic and professional activities, he has lectured at seminars addressing litigation issues.  He also serves as a member of the Board of Directors of the Atlanta Committee for UNICEF.
<P>
Mr. Schneider attended the United States Naval Academy Preparatory
School from 1974 to 1975, and the United States Naval Academy from 1975
to 1977, and graduated magna cum laude from Auburn University with a
B.A. in English in 1978.  In 1981, Mr. Schneider graduated summa cum
laude from Mercer University Walter F. George School of Law.
