<CENTER><H3><B>Laurence V. Senn, Jr.</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/senn.jpg">

Larry Senn joined King & Spalding as a partner in 1995 and is head of the Litigation Practice in New York. He was formerly a senior litigation partner at Mudge Rose in New York, where he held the position of Chairman of the Litigation Department.
<P>
Mr. Senn has a broad based commercial litigation background, as well as
extensive experience in the nuclear power industry. He has handled lawsuits
arising out of the original design and construction of eight different
nuclear power stations and currently is involved in a number of disputes
concerning long term power purchase contracts.
<P>
Mr. Senn received his B.A. in 1965 and his J.D in 1969 from the University
of North Carolina where he was Associate Editor of the <EM>North Carolina
Law Review </EM>and a member of the Order of the Coif. From 1982-1990 he
co-chaired a Practicing Law Institute program concerning complex commercial
litigation. He currently serves as a court-appointed mediator for the
federal district court for the Southern District of New York and as a
court-appointed arbitrator for the Eastern District of New York. He is a
member of the New York, New Jersey and District of Columbia Bars.
