<CENTER><H3><B>Richard L. Shackelford</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/shcklfdr.jpg">

Rick Shackelford is a member of King & Spalding's Commercial Litigation group and a member of the Firm's Healthcare Practice Group.  He joined the Firm in 1985 and was elected partner in 1987.
<P>
Mr. Shackelford's practice has involved a wide variety of civil and
regulatory litigation with an emphasis in healthcare litigation.
His healthcare litigation practice has focused on certificate of need,
licensure and certification, reimbursement and medical staff disputes.
<P>
He has been involved in several internal corporate investigations and
in complex commercial litigation matters.  He has advised healthcare
providers, pharmaceutical companies and medical device companies in
such areas as reimbursement, fraud and abuse, managed care and health
planning.
<P>
Mr. Shackelford has written and lectured on healthcare
law issues and is a member of the American Academy of Hospital Attorneys
and the National Health Lawyers Association.  He serves on the Board
of Directors of the Georgia Academy of Hospital Attorneys.
<P>
Mr. Shackelford graduated summa cum laude from the University of Georgia
in 1976.  He graduated summa cum laude from the University of Georgia
School of Law in 1979.
