<HEADER>
<TITLE>Abraham N.M. "Hap" Shashy</TITLE>
</HEADER><body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>Abraham N.M. "Hap" Shashy</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/shashy.jpg">

Hap Shashy is a tax partner in the Washington, D.C. office of King
& Spalding.  He joined the Firm in 1993 after completing his appointment
as Chief Counsel for the Internal Revenue Service from February 1990
through January 1993.
<P>
Mr. Shashy has experience in a broad array of federal income tax areas,
including large case litigation and settlement (including transfer pricing),
alternative dispute resolution tax, corporate tax and consolidated returns,
partnership tax, taxation of financial instruments, commodities, oil
and gas tax, tax accounting, and taxation of inbound and outbound international
transactions.
<P>
Mr. Shashy received his B.S. in Political Science from the University
of Florida with highest honors in 1970, and received his J.D. with high
honors from the University of Florida School of Law in 1973.  In 1975,
Mr. Shashy received his L.L.M. in Taxation from New York University
School of Law where he served as Managing Editor of the <EM>Tax Law Review.</EM>
From 1975-1976 he taught full-time in the Graduate Tax Program at New
York University School of Law.  From 1976 until 1984, he served as an
adjunct professor in the Tax Program while practicing law in New York
City.
<P>
