<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Harold M. Shaw</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#00009c" VLINK="#8e2323">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER></CENTER>
<HR>
<CENTER>
<H3><B>Harold M. Shaw</B></H3></CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/shaw.jpg" ALIGN="LEFT">
<P>Harold Shaw joined King &amp; Spalding in 1989 and became counsel in 1993.
His practice focuses on environmental, health, and safety compliance, the
development of corporate compliance programs, and environmental matters in
commercial transactions. </P>
<P>Examples of his practice include the following:</P>
<UL>
<LI> Mr. Shaw handles environmental, health, and safety matters in the context
of commercial, financial, and real estate transactions. He represents lenders,
purchasers, borrowers, and developers. In the context of these projects, he
inspects sites, works with technical consultants, conducts due diligence
reviews, drafts documents, and conducts negotiations. This work necessarily
requires Mr. Shaw to identify and address matters that arise under any type of
environmental or health and safety requirement.
<P></P></LI>
<LI> Mr. Shaw assists clients in developing and implementing corporate
compliance programs. He has drafted a number of environmental and general
compliance programs and has conducted on-site compliance reviews to assist
clients in identifying and correcting potential deficiencies.
<P></P></LI>
<LI> Mr. Shaw provides environmental and OSHA compliance advice to numerous
corporate clients. In particular, he assists companies with hazardous and solid
waste issues under the Resource Conservation and Recovery Act. He regularly
handles Clean Water Act matters.  His experience also involves international
environmental requirements, regulation of environmental advertising, and Clean
Air Act matters, particularly with respect to CFCs.
<P></P></LI>
<LI> Mr. Shaw represents companies in their dealings with government agencies
and courts. This representation includes preparation of comments in rulemaking
proceedings, as well as litigation challenging final rules. Mr. Shaw has
represented clients in environmental enforcement actions and administrative
proceedings, including cases where the government has sought to bar a company
from government contract work.
</LI></UL>
<P>Mr. Shaw graduated from Georgetown University Law Center (magna cum laude),
where he was an editor of the <I>Georgetown Law Journal</I>. He holds an
undergraduate degree (cum laude) from Dickinson College. Mr. Shaw served in the
Judge Advocate General's Corps of the United States Navy.</P>
<P><A HREF="/menu/envir.htm">Environmental Practice</A></P>
