<HTML>
<HEADER>
<TITLE>Horace H. Sibley</TITLE>
</HEADER><body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>Horace H. Sibley</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/sibleyh.jpg">

Horace Sibley joined King & Spalding in 1967 and became a partner in 1972. He served in the Corporate Department working on acquisitions and mergers until 1992, when he joined the newly created Intellectual Property & Technology Group. Mr. Sibley is responsible for coordinating the Firm's practice in Japan, China and throughout the Pacific Rim, and is currently responsible for the Firm's representation of the Atlanta Committee for the Olympic Games. In this capacity, he has recently negotiated television rights agreements with broadcasters throughout the Pacific Rim including Japan, Korea, the Philippines, and Taiwan, and the countries included in the Asian Broadcast Union.
<P>
He was one of the original three members of the group in Atlanta who organized the effort to bring the 1996 Summer Olympics to Atlanta. Mr. Sibley was on the Executive Committee and was Chairman of the International Affairs Committee of the Atlanta Organizing Committee. He is currently a member of the Board of the Atlanta Committee for the Olympic Games. He has served as Chairman of the Board of Egleston Children's Hospital at Emory, the largest children's hospital in the Southeast. 
<P>
Mr. Sibley is currently Chairman of the Board of the Georgia Center for Advanced Telecommunications Technology - a unique partnership of academia, industry and government which coordinates the state's economic development efforts in the rapidly converging advanced telecommunications industries of cable television, computing, consumer electronics, content origination/broadcasting and telecommunications.
<P>
He has served on the Board of Trustees of Leadership Georgia and participated in Leadership Atlanta and the 
International Business Fellows Program. Mr. Sibley has served as a Director of the Rotary Club of Atlanta. He is a Board member of the Southern Center for International Studies.
<P>
Born in Philadelphia, Pennsylvania, Mr. Sibley earned a Bachelor's Degree from Vanderbilt University; a Doctor of Laws Degree from the University of Georgia with distinction, where he was Editor-in-Chief of the law school's <EM>Law Journal</EM>; and a Master of Business Administration Degree from Georgia State University. During the years 1964 through 1966, he served as a Captain in the U.S. Army Infantry where he received the Army Commendation Medal for Meritorious Service.
<P>
<P>
<A HREF="/menu/ipt.htm">Intellectual Property & Technology Practice</A><P>
