<HEADER>
<TITLE>Gordon A. Smith</TITLE>
</HEADER><body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>Gordon A. Smith</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/smithg.jpg">
<P>
Gordon Smith is a litigation partner with extensive trial experience
in several substantive areas including products liability, environmental,
general litigation and regulatory proceedings.
<P>
In recent years, Mr. Smith has concentrated in the defense of products
liability cases on behalf of manufacturers.  He has tried cases on behalf
of automobile manufacturers in California, New Jersey, North Carolina,
South Carolina and Georgia.
<P>
Mr. Smith has acted as coordinating counsel for a major tobacco products
company and has coordinated the defense of more than 50
tobacco products liability cases.  Mr. Smith is presently lead counsel on behalf of various manufacturers in cases pending in Texas, Mississippi, Alabama, Tennessee, Florida, Georgia, North Carolina and New Jersey.  Additionally, Mr. Smith has substantial experience in issues of employment law, media law and the First Amendment.
<P>
Mr. Smith is co-chair of the American Bar Association, Section of Litigation,
Product Liability Committee and is a member of the Board of Governors
of the State Bar of Georgia.  He is also a member of the Bar Council
of the United States District Court for the Northern District of Georgia.
Mr. Smith is a frequent speaker at seminars sponsored by many prominent
groups, including the ABA Product Liability Committee Midyear Meeting,
the Defense Research Institute, and the Institute of Continuing Legal
Education in Georgia.  He is a sustaining member of the Product Liability
Advisory Committee.
<P>
Mr. Smith joined King & Spalding in 1980, after a clerkship with the
Honorable William C. O'Kelley, Chief Judge of the United States District
Court for the Northern District of Georgia.  Mr. Smith graduated from
the University of Georgia in 1975 and the University of Georgia School
of Law in 1978.
<P>
<P>
