<CENTER><H3><B>Reginald R. Smith</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/smithr.jpg">
<P>
Reggie Smith joined King & Spalding in 1987, was elected partner in 1994 and is currently engaged with the Firm's Litigation Practice in the Houston office. He has experience in business dispute litigation such as commercial fraud, RICO, antitrust, and lender liability matters. Mr. Smith's practice includes litigation, arbitration, and mediation. His litigation experience has involved a wide range of complex commercial civil disputes, including major litigation in both state and federal courts.
<P>
Mr. Smith is a member of the Business Torts Litigation Committee of the Section of Litigation of the American Bar Association, including its Civil RICO Subcommittee for which he has engaged in professional writing and a seminar presentation.
<P>
Mr. Smith received his J.D., magna cum laude, from the University of Georgia (1987). He is a 1984 graduate, summa cum laude, from Emory University, where he also received his M.A. degree. He is a member of the State Bars of Texas and Georgia.
