<TITLE>Robert L. Steed</TITLE>
</HEADER><body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>Robert L. Steed</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/steed.jpg">
<P>
Bob Steed is head of King & Spalding's Public Finance Group.  He serves as bond counsel to the State of Georgia and to cities, counties and governmental authorities throughout the state and the Southeast. <P>
He has worked in public finance law for over 30 years and argued the test case before the Georgia Supreme Court which authorized the State to issue general obligation debt. Mr. Steed serves on the Committee on Tax-Exempt Finance of the Taxation Section of the American Bar Association.<P>
Mr. Steed is active in civic activities and recently completed a five year term as Chairman of the Board of Trustees of Mercer University. His humor columns have appeared for many years in <EM>The Atlanta Constitution </EM>and in papers of the New York Times Regional Newspaper Group. <P>

Mr. Steed graduated from Mercer University in 1958. He received his law degree from Walter F. George School of Law of Mercer University in 1961.  He serves as Treasurer of the Walter F. George Foundation and is a Co-Trustee of the law school's George W. Woodruff Trust.  In 1961-1962, Mr Steed served as Law Clerk to Justice Carlton Mobley on the Supreme Court of Georgia.  He joined King & Spalding in 1962 and became a partner in 1967.  He holds an Honorary Doctor of Laws from Mercer University.
<P>
