<HEADER>
<TITLE>Jeffrey M. Stein</TITLE>
</HEADER><body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>Jeffrey M. Stein</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/stein.jpg">

Jeff Stein has experience in a broad range of corporate finance transactions
and securities matters, particularly in the area of public offerings.
Mr. Stein has represented corporate issuers and underwriters in "shelf"
registrations of investment-grade debt securities, medium-term note
programs, high-yield securities offerings and initial public offerings
of common stock.  Related types of financings have included institutional
private placements under Rule 144A and offshore offerings under Regulation
S.
<P>
Mr. Stein has counselled corporations in interest rate swaps, currency
swaps and other transactions in derivatives.  He also practices in the
area of aircraft finance, where he has represented airlines, lenders
and underwriters in leveraged lease transactions, with both privately
placed and publicly-offered debt participation.  Mr. Stein also advises
corporate clients regarding SEC reporting, securities transactions and
other compliance matters.
<P>
Admitted to practice in Georgia and New York, Mr. Stein is a member
of the State Bar of Georgia, and the New York State, Atlanta, and 
American Bar Associations.  He is a member of the Legal Opinions Committees
of the American Bar Association (Section of Business Law) and the State
Bar of Georgia (Corporate and Banking Law Section) and has recently
been appointed to the Tri-Bar Legal Opinion Committee of the New York
City, County and State Bar Associations.  Mr. Stein has conducted Bar
seminars on the subjects of legal opinions and public offerings.
<P>
Mr. Stein graduated from Yeshiva University with a B.A. in 1977 and
received his J.D. from Harvard University in 1980.  He practiced in
New York City from 1980-1985.  He joined King & Spalding in 1985 and was elected partner in 1988.  He currently practices
in Atlanta.
<P>
<P>
<A HREF="/menu/corp.htm">Corporate Practice</A><P>
