<HTML>
<HEADER>
<TITLE>Mason W. Stephenson</TITLE>
</HEADER><body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>Mason W. Stephenson</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/stephens.jpg">

Mason Stephenson is a partner in King & Spalding's Commercial Real Estate Practice Group which is comprised of approximately 25 lawyers. 
<P>
During his more than twenty years of practice, he has represented banks, credit companies, life insurance companies, pension funds and other institutional investors in consummating secured financings and equity investments in income properties, including office buildings, hotels, apartments and industrial properties. He has extensive experience in the workout, restructure and foreclosure of real estate investments, including both loan and partnership relationships. 
<P>
More recently, Mr. Stephenson has represented investors in the acquisition of portfolios of financial and real estate assets from the Resolution Trust Corporation, the Department of Housing and Urban Development and other institutions.
<P>
Mr. Stephenson received his B.A. degree, cum laude, in 1968 from Davidson College where he was elected to Phi Beta Kappa and his law degree in 1971 from The University of Chicago Law School. He was an Associate Editor of <EM>The University of Chicago Law Review. </EM>
<P>
Mr. Stephenson has served as a member of the Executive Committee of the Real Estate Section of the State Bar of Georgia since 1989 and previously served as Chairman of the Atlanta Bar Association's Real Estate Section (1981-82). He is a frequent lecturer on commercial real estate and ethics topics. He was elected a member of the American College of Real Estate Lawyers in 1993.<P>
<P>
<A HREF="/menu/real.htm">Real Estate Practice</A><P>
<p><center>
<HR>
</center><p><center>
</a>
