<HEADER>
<TITLE>Peter K. Storey</TITLE>
</HEADER><body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>Peter K. Storey</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/storey.jpg">

Peter Storey joined King & Spalding in 1992 as a partner in the New
York office.  He concentrates his practice in the area of bank lending (secured and unsecured), project financing and other forms of negotiated institutional financing, with particular emphasis on credit enhancement, exempt securities, derivatives and structured cash flows financing transactions.
<P>
Mr. Storey has extensive bank regulatory experience, and a significant
portion of his practice is devoted to issues involving foreign banks
and foreign legal environments.
<P>
A 1977 graduate with distinction from Stanford University, he received
a masters degree in Business Administration and a law degree, cum laude,
from Cornell University in 1982.
<P>
<P>
<A HREF="/menu/bankfin.htm">Banking & Finance Practice </A><P>
