<HEADER>
<TITLE>Jess H. Stribling</TITLE>
</HEADER><body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>Jess H. Stribling</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/striblin.jpg">

Jess Stribling is the Partner in Charge of King & Spalding's Washington, D.C. Office and practices in the Firm's Food and Drug Group.  He represents human and veterinary drug, medical device and cosmetic companies, contract research organizations, blood banks, and narcotic treatment centers in their dealings with the Food and Drug Administration, the Drug Enforcement Administration, and
the Congress.  Mr. Stribling is counsel and executive director of the Animal Drug Alliance, an association of animal drug companies.
<P>
Prior to entering private practice, he served in the FDA Chief Counsel's
Office as Associate Chief Counsel for Veterinary Medicine, Associate
Chief Counsel for Foods, and Deputy Chief Counsel for Administration.
He was appointed Executive Assistant to the Commissioner by Arthur
Hull Hayes and served in that capacity under Acting Commissioner Mark
Novitch and for a time under Commissioner Frank Young.  He is a recipient
of the agency's highest award, the FDA Award of Merit.
<P>
Mr. Stribling is a graduate of the University of North Carolina (1959)
and a cum laude graduate of the George Washington University Law School
(1974).  Upon graduation, he served as law clerk to the Honorable Judge Oliver Gasch
of the U.S. District Court for the District of Columbia.
<P>
<P>
<A HREF="/menu/food.htm">Food & Drug Practice</A><P>
