<HEADER>
<TITLE>Erik J. Swenson</TITLE>
</HEADER><body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>Erik J. Swenson</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/swenson.jpg">
<P>
Mr. Swenson is counsel to King & Spalding in the New York office. He regularly represents industrial companies with regard to energy matters, including the purchase and sale of electricity.  His practice also includes the representation of project lenders, equity investors and developers in numerous aspects of acquisition, development, investment and regulation relating to energy production facilities, international and domestic.
<P>
From 1983 to 1987, Mr. Swenson practiced law in Washington, D.C., where his focus was on  the self-regulation of a large multinational corporation's operations in Africa, Asia, Europe and the Americas; the opening of the communications industry to competition; and the regulation of energy projects at the federal level.
<P>
From 1987 to the present, Mr. Swenson's practice has been based in New York. During this period, he has assisted numerous IPP developers in negotiating key project contracts and obtaining financing, participated in administrative and court proceedings to uphold the rights of IPP developers, lenders and industrial electric consumers under federal and state energy laws, and advised large electric consumers, lenders, equity investors, power marketers and a rating agency with respect to specific energy projects and the energy industry generally.
<P>
Mr. Swenson has lectured before key energy industry leaders on project development and energy regulation. He has also contributed to the <EM>Electricity Yearbook </EM>published by Executive Enterprises Publications Co., Inc., <EM>Competitive Utility </EM>published by Information Forecast, Inc., and other publications widely read by those active in the energy industry.
<P>
Mr. Swenson attended the United States Air Force Academy and graduated cum laude from Columbia College with a degree in geology. He also holds the degree of Juris Doctor from the Columbia University School of Law.
<P>
<P>
<A HREF="/menu/energy.htm">Energy & Independent Power Practice</A><P>
