<HEADER>
<TITLE>William C. Talmadge</TITLE>
</HEADER><body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>William C. Talmadge</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/talmadge.jpg">

Bill Talmadge joined King & Spalding in 1987.  He is counsel in the Washington, D.C., office, within the Firm's Governmental Practice Group.
<P>
Mr. Talmadge has represented clients across a broad range of issues
including defense, healthcare, campaign finance law, and food and drug
matters before committees of Congress, federal agencies and state legislatures.
Working in concert with King & Spalding attorneys, his practice has
involved not only standard legislative advocacy, but also the drafting
of statutes and regulations, the preparation of public comment on proposed
regulations, and the preparation of committee report language.
<P>
He worked in the Public Affairs Department of The Coca-Cola Company,
where he was involved with legislative and regulatory issues at the
federal level, and lobbied state legislative issues, working at one
time or another in more than 20 state legislatures.  He was campaign
manager of the Georgia gubernatorial campaign of the Honorable Ronald
B. Ginn, and served as Administrative Assistant to Congressman Richard
B. Ray.
<P>
A graduate of the University of North Carolina, he earned his J.D.
from the University of Georgia School of Law in 1967.  Mr. Talmadge
served as law clerk to Chief Justice Bond Almand of the Georgia Supreme
Court, and Legislative Assistant to United States Senator Herman Talmadge.
<P>
<P>
<A HREF="/menu/govaff.htm">Governmental Affairs Practice</A><P>
