<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Philip A. Theodore</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#00009c" VLINK="#8e2323">
<P></P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER></CENTER>
<HR>
<CENTER>
<H3><B>Philip A. Theodore</B></H3></CENTER><IMG
ALIGN="LEFT" VSPACE="10" HSPACE="10" SRC="/gif/theodore.jpg">
<P>Phil Theodore is a member of the Firm's corporate practice in Atlanta. He
joined King &amp; Spalding in 1981 and became a partner in 1986.  He has
extensive experience in matters relating to the Securities Act of 1933 and the
Securities Exchange Act of 1934, gained from representing a number of public and
private companies in complex financial transactions, including equity and debt
offerings, acquisitions and reorganizations.  For example, Mr. Theodore
represented the issuers of securities in the following highly complex financial
transactions:</P>
<UL>
<LI> $1.6 billion leveraged buy-out of a large medical corporation in 1988,
which involved registered offerings of $240 million of Senior Discount Notes and
$355 million of Senior Subordinated Debentures;
<P></P></LI>
<LI> $1.2 billion financial restructuring of a large medical corporation in
1992, which involved a registered solicitation of consents to a pre-packaged
bankruptcy proceeding;
<P></P></LI>
<LI> $375 million private offering of Senior Subordinated Debentures for a
large medical corporation and subsequent registered exchange offer;
<P></P></LI>
<LI> Form S-4 registrations of shares of Common Stock of a large medical
conglamerate in 1996 in connection with two significant acquisitions; and
<P></P></LI>
<LI> Registered exchange offer of Common Stock for Convertible Subordinated
Debentures of a large international airline corporation.
<P></P></LI></UL>
<P>Mr. Theodore graduated from the University of Tennessee at Chattanooga in
1975. He received his law degree from the University of Cincinnati in 1978.  Mr.
Theodore was Editor-in- Chief of <I>The University of Cincinnati Law Review
</I>and was a member of the Order of the Coif.</P>
<P><A HREF="/menu/corp.htm">Corporate Practice</A></P>
