<HEADER>
<TITLE>Larry D. Thompson</TITLE>
</HEADER><body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>Larry D. Thompson</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/thompson.jpg">

A member of the Special Matters Practice, Larry Thompson practiced
at King & Spalding from 1977-82 and then served four years as the United
States Attorney for the Northern District of Georgia.  As a United States
Attorney, he directed the Southeastern Organized Crime Drug Enforcement
Task Force and served on the Attorney General's Economic Crime Council.
<P>
After returning to King & Spalding in 1986 as a partner, Mr. Thompson
resumed his practice in civil and criminal law.  He has represented
businesses and individuals in a wide variety of matters, including grand
jury proceedings, internal corporate investigations and trials.  He
represented at trial a corporation charged with submitting a false document
to the government, and recently represented several defense contractors
in investigative matters.
<P>
Mr. Thompson is a member of the Board of Directors of the Northern
District of Georgia Federal Offender Program, the State of Georgia Bar
Examiners, and the Lawyers Advisory Committee of the Eleventh Circuit
Court of Appeals.  He has written and lectured on civil litigation techniques,
litigation ethics, RICO, bank fraud and white collar crime.  He edited
an American Bar Association publication entitled <EM>Jury Instructions in
Criminal Antitrust Cases, 1976-1980.</EM>
<P>
Mr. Thompson graduated cum laude from Culver-Stockton College in 1967.
He received his Masters Degree from Michigan State University in 1969
and his law degree from the University of Michigan in 1974.
<P>
<P>
<A HREF="/menu/special.htm">Special Matters Practice</A><P>
