<HEADER>
<TITLE>M. Robert Thornton</TITLE>
</HEADER><body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>M. Robert Thornton</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/thornton.jpg">

Robert Thornton is a partner in the General Litigation Practice. He joined King & Spalding in 1976 and was elected partner in 1984. 
<P>
Although having extensive general experience as a civil litigator, his practice has focused emphasis in the areas of shareholder claims, director and officer liability and insurance, securities, SEC investigations, professional liability, and legal ethics.
<P>
Mr. Thornton has represented acquiring companies, acquired companies, controlling shareholders, minority shareholders, directors and officers, and special committees of directors in connection with shareholder class and derivative claims involving mergers and acquisitions, going private transactions, and other significant corporate events. He has also defended a variety of shareholder class actions and related derivative suits alleging violations of the federal and state securities laws and related state law fiduciary claims. He has litigated such cases in various state and federal courts around the country, including the Delaware Court of Chancery. 
<P>
Mr. Thornton received his J.D., cum laude, in 1976 from Harvard Law School. He earned a bachelor's degree, cum laude, in 1973 from Princeton University.
<P>
<A HREF="/menu/comlit.htm">Commercial Litigation Practice</A><P>
