<HEADER>
<TITLE>Charles H. Tisdale, Jr.</TITLE>
</HEADER><body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>Charles H. Tisdale, Jr.</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/tisdale.jpg">

Chet Tisdale has practiced environmental law at King & Spalding since 1973 and has represented clients on air, water, and waste issues before state and federal agencies and in litigation.
<P>
His superfund experience includes:
<UL>
<LI>chairperson of steering committees at nine sites;
<LI>common counsel for generator groups at five sites;
<LI>service as an arbitrator or mediator to allocate costs among parties at fifteen sites;
<LI>appointment by U.S. District Court as Special Master for allocation among generators; and
<LI>representation of individual parties in more than fifty superfund sites.
</UL>
<P>
His water and hazardous waste practice includes:
<UL>
<LI>representation of Georgia pulp and paper mills in a successful challenge to EPA's proposed water quality standard for dioxin;
<LI>representation of coalition of local governments in establishing alternative limits for metals in NPDES permits;
<LI>representing industries in successful defense of citizen suit claims involving NPDES 
<LI>permit discharges; and
<LI>representation of porcelain enamel companies in a RCRA rulemaking petition which overturned EPA's efforts to extend its hazardous waste regulations to porcelain and enamel waste. See decision reported at 51 F.R. 19320 (May 28, 1986).
</UL>
<P>Mr. Tisdale is a member of the Board of Editors of the <EM>Chemical Waste Litigation Reporter.</EM><P>
<P>
<A HREF="/menu/envir.htm">Environmental Practice</A><P>
