<HEADER>
<TITLE>Carmen R. Toledo</TITLE>
</HEADER><body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>Carmen R. Toledo</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/toledo.jpg">

Carmen Toledo is counsel to King & Spalding in the Atlanta office, where she concentrates in toxic tort and product liability matters.
<P>
In the toxic tort area, she has handled cases dealing with various chemicals, including dioxin, toxaphene, chlorine and chlordane as well as TCE and other solvents.
<P>
In addition to toxic tort matters, Ms. Toledo has been involved in litigation for various pharmaceutical companies' product liability cases, including IUD and DES cases for major automobile and cigarette manufacturers.
<P>
Ms. Toledo received her law degree from Yale in 1987 and her undergraduate degree from the University of California-Davis in 1983.  Upon graduation she commenced practice in Los Angeles with Sidley & Austin and joined King & Spalding's Toxic Tort & Product Liability Practice in 1991.  Prior to law school, Ms. Toledo was a legal secretary and assistant in Sacramento and in Davis, California.
<P>
Ms. Toledo is admitted to practice in Georgia and California, in the Central and Southern Districts of California, and in the Northern District of Georgia and the United States Court of Appeals for the Ninth Circuit.<P>
<P>
<A HREF="/menu/toxic.htm">Toxic Tort Practice</A><P>
