<HEAD>
<TITLE>John A. Wallace</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#00009c" VLINK="#8e2323">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER></CENTER>
<HR>
<CENTER>
<H3><B>John A. Wallace</B></H3></CENTER><IMG
ALIGN="LEFT" VSPACE="10" HSPACE="10" SRC="/gif/wallace.jpg">
<P>John Wallace is a partner concentrating in trusts and estates.  He has
practiced with King &amp; Spalding for over 30 years.  He is a graduate of
Princeton University and Harvard Law School.</P>
<P>Mr. Wallace has been a frequent lecturer and panel member at many tax
institutes, conferences and other continuing education programs.  He served as
an adjunct professor at Emory University Law School between 1977 and 1987,
teaching the Advanced Estate Planning course in the Graduate Tax Program.</P>
<P>His most recent publications include <I>Selected Post-Death Problems of
Partnerships and Partners,</I> 1981 Southern California Tax Institute, <I>Estate
Tax Deferral: Does Postponement Produce Panacea or Perplexity,</I> 1982 Miami
Estate Planning Institute, and <I>Now You See It, Now You Don't -- Valuation
Conundrums in Estate Planning,</I> 1990 Miami Estate Planning Institute.</P>
<P>Mr. Wallace is a Past President of The American College of Trust and Estate
Counsel and Past Chair of the Section of Real Property, Probate and Trust Law of
the American Bar Association.  He currently is a member of the House of
Delegates of the American Bar Association.  He is a member of the International
Academy of Estate and Trust Law, the American College of Tax Counsel, the
American Law Institute and the American Bar Foundation.  Mr. Wallace is a Past
Chairman of the Fiduciary Law Section of the State Bar of Georgia and a Past
President of both the Southern Pension Conference and the Atlanta Estate
Planning Council, Inc.</P>
<P>Mr. Wallace serves as Vice-Chair of the Board of Trustees of Piedmont
Medical Center, Inc. and as a Trustee of PROMINA Health System, The Westminister
Schools, Fernbank Museum of Natural History, and Morehouse College, all located
in Atlanta. </P>
<P><A HREF="/menu/trusts.htm">Trusts &amp; Estates Practice</A></P>
