<HEADER>
<TITLE>Thomas F. Wessel</TITLE>
</HEADER><body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>Thomas F. Wessel</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/wessel.jpg">

Tom Wessel is a partner in the Tax Practice Group of King & Spalding. Resident in the Washington D.C. office, he practices in numerous areas of federal income taxation, including corporate tax, with a particular emphasis on mergers and acquisitions, restructuring transactions, debt and equity offerings, consolidated returns, taxation of financial instruments, partnership taxation and tax accounting.
<P>
Prior to joining King & Spalding in 1991, Mr. Wessel was Special Counsel to the Chief Counsel at the Internal Revenue Service (1990-1991) where he served as the principal legal advisor to the Chief Counsel. He had also served as Attorney-Advisor (1985-1987) and Associate Tax Legislative Counsel (1988-1989) in the Office of Tax Legislative Counsel at the U.S. Treasury Department, where he had primary responsibility for the development of legislation and regulatory guidance in the area of corporate taxation.
<P>
Mr. Wessel is an active member of the American Bar Association Section of Taxation where he served as a co-chair of the Corporate Tax Subcommittee for Policy and Special Projects (1991-1994) and the Chair of the Corporate Tax Subcommittee on Tax-Free Reorganizations (1995-1996). He currently serves as a Vice-Chair of the Committee on Corporate Tax and also is a member of the American Bar Association Section of Taxation and Government Relations Committee. He regularly speaks on subjects in his practice areas at forums such as the Practising Law Institute, Tax Executives Institute, New York University, Atlanta Tax Forum, Federal Bar Association, American Law Institute, and American Bar Association.
<P>
Mr. Wessel graduated magna cum laude from the University of Pennsylvania, The Wharton School, where he was elected to Beta Alpha Psi. He graduated cum laude from New York University School of Law, where he served on the <EM>New York University Law Review </EM>and was a member of the Order of the Coif. Mr. Wessel also received his LL.M. in Taxation from New York University.
<P>
<P>
<A HREF="/menu/tax.htm">Tax Practice</A><P>
