<HTML>
<HEADER>
<TITLE>Ruth Tinsley West</TITLE>
</HEADER><body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/k-s2b.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><HR></CENTER>
<CENTER><H3><B>Ruth Tinsley West</B></H3></CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10 SRC="/gif/west.jpg">

Ruth West has practiced in the area of public finance since she joined King & Spalding in 1974 (she was elected partner in 1980).  During that time her practice has focused primarily on serving as bond counsel for tax-exempt industrial revenue bond transactions, including small exempt issues and exempt facilities bonds.  In that connection she has rendered her opinion as bond counsel in over 30 states.
<P>
Ms. West has substantial experience in structuring taxable municipal transactions, including those structured to obtain maximum ad valorem tax incentives.  She also has acted as bond counsel in connection with hospital financings and traditional municipal financings.  In addition, she frequently serves as underwriter's counsel and represents financial institutions in several capacities as private placement agents, credit enhancers and remarketing agents.
<P>
Ms. West has served as Director and Treasurer of the National Association of Bond Lawyers, as a member of the Steering Committee and Chairman of the Bond Attorneys' Workshop and as Chairman of the Legislative Seminar of the National Association of Bond Lawyers.  She serves on the Committee on Tax-Exempt Finance of the Taxation Section of the American Bar Association.<P>
She has served as a member of the Board on many professional and civic associations, including the Lawyers Club of Atlanta, the Georgia Justice Project, Mercer University Press, the Georgia Bar Foundation, the Georgia Center for Children and the Atlanta Women's Fund.  She has served on the Board of Visitors of Mercer Law School and as President of its Alumni Association.
<P>
Ms. West graduated from Duke University in 1966 and received her law degree, cum laude, in 1974 from the Walter F. George School of Law of Mercer University, where she was the Editor-in-Chief of the <EM>Mercer Law Review.</EM>
<P>
<P>
<A HREF="/menu/pubfin.htm">Public Finance Practice</A><P>
<p><center>
<HR>
</center><p><center>
</a>
